1
00:00:01,290 --> 00:00:09,700
<b>Hotel Del Luna Blu-ray Disc 3</b>
Subtitle re-timing by Jharel

2
00:00:58,684 --> 00:00:59,734
{\an8}Chan-sung!

3
00:01:03,981 --> 00:01:05,071
{\an8}Don't look.

4
00:01:07,109 --> 00:01:08,569
{\an8}Don't let her hear your breathing.

5
00:01:09,111 --> 00:01:10,241
{\an8}But I hear--

6
00:01:11,822 --> 00:01:12,822
{\an8}Don't listen to it.

7
00:01:18,954 --> 00:01:19,964
What's the matter?

8
00:02:10,047 --> 00:02:11,507
She's the guest staying in this room.

9
00:02:12,841 --> 00:02:14,341
You'll go mad if you see her.

10
00:02:17,012 --> 00:02:18,722
Don't turn around.

11
00:02:20,474 --> 00:02:22,104
Get out of here once the door opens.

12
00:02:38,283 --> 00:02:39,163
Go.

13
00:02:58,887 --> 00:02:59,887
Ma'am.

14
00:03:04,976 --> 00:03:08,016
You won't ever be able
to step out of that door.

15
00:03:08,980 --> 00:03:10,940
I apologize for waking you up.

16
00:03:11,358 --> 00:03:14,068
Why don't you go back inside
and get some sleep?

17
00:03:32,212 --> 00:03:35,092
I guess the smell of incense
made you go crazy.

18
00:03:40,554 --> 00:03:43,934
You've been locked up
in that closet for such a long time.

19
00:03:44,182 --> 00:03:47,062
And you still get angry
when you see a human being?

20
00:03:49,062 --> 00:03:50,982
Do you want to go outside
and vent your anger again?

21
00:03:57,946 --> 00:03:59,406
You're a guest here.

22
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:02,240
So I won't shove you in the closet.

23
00:04:02,325 --> 00:04:04,325
You should quietly crawl back inside
on your own.

24
00:04:27,267 --> 00:04:28,517
Koo Chan-sung.

25
00:04:30,604 --> 00:04:31,814
Koo Chan-sung.

26
00:04:40,238 --> 00:04:41,358
Koo Chan-sung.

27
00:04:43,325 --> 00:04:44,575
<i>Koo Chan-sung.</i>

28
00:04:51,666 --> 00:04:52,916
<i>Koo Chan-sung.</i>

29
00:04:56,254 --> 00:04:57,464
Jang Man-wol?

30
00:04:59,007 --> 00:05:00,257
<i>Koo Chan-sung.</i>

31
00:05:02,135 --> 00:05:03,595
Koo Chan-sung.

32
00:05:06,223 --> 00:05:08,063
Stop being stupid.

33
00:05:08,391 --> 00:05:10,981
You don't know what a coward he is.

34
00:05:12,145 --> 00:05:15,725
No matter how many times you call him,
he won't come back.

35
00:05:23,073 --> 00:05:24,123
Chan-sung?

36
00:05:26,618 --> 00:05:27,788
Jang Man-wol!

37
00:06:09,744 --> 00:06:13,794
Was that Mr. Third Choice
who ran out at lightning speed?

38
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:18,340
Even if you look with one eye closed,
it's not Mr. Koo.

39
00:06:18,420 --> 00:06:21,380
I thought so too.
The hair was all loose and wild.

40
00:06:21,464 --> 00:06:23,094
It's the guest in Room 13.

41
00:06:24,342 --> 00:06:25,802
She has left the hotel.

42
00:06:25,885 --> 00:06:29,385
Our plan has failed. This is a disaster.

43
00:06:45,572 --> 00:06:46,702
Chan-sung.

44
00:06:48,700 --> 00:06:50,040
That thing is not here.

45
00:06:51,703 --> 00:06:52,793
You can let me go.

46
00:07:06,426 --> 00:07:07,426
You...

47
00:07:08,678 --> 00:07:09,848
saw it, didn't you?

48
00:07:11,473 --> 00:07:12,473
Just a glimpse.

49
00:07:15,101 --> 00:07:17,151
So have you gone crazy?

50
00:07:17,854 --> 00:07:18,984
I'm not crazy.

51
00:07:19,564 --> 00:07:22,154
I was so frightened
that I can't calm myself down now.

52
00:07:23,777 --> 00:07:25,777
What about you? Are you hurt?

53
00:07:26,988 --> 00:07:28,158
Are you all right, Man-wol?

54
00:07:33,036 --> 00:07:34,156
Chan-sung.

55
00:07:37,457 --> 00:07:38,377
Were you scared?

56
00:07:41,252 --> 00:07:42,342
I'm not hurt.

57
00:07:42,420 --> 00:07:43,340
I'm fine.

58
00:07:45,423 --> 00:07:46,343
Why you...

59
00:07:47,133 --> 00:07:49,053
You've gone a little crazy.

60
00:07:49,135 --> 00:07:50,715
I was just playing around.

61
00:07:52,138 --> 00:07:53,518
Were you really scared?

62
00:07:55,976 --> 00:07:59,056
Then, is it really true that you go mad

63
00:07:59,145 --> 00:08:00,515
if you see that ghost?

64
00:08:00,605 --> 00:08:03,225
I thought you said that just to scare me.

65
00:08:03,608 --> 00:08:05,988
Yes, it's true.

66
00:08:06,319 --> 00:08:08,529
If you had seen it properly,

67
00:08:08,613 --> 00:08:10,453
you would've gone completely mad.

68
00:08:10,532 --> 00:08:11,572
Really?

69
00:08:14,244 --> 00:08:15,874
She's really left, right?

70
00:08:16,871 --> 00:08:18,161
Yes, she ran away.

71
00:08:18,248 --> 00:08:21,328
I thought you'd take care of it.
How could you let her go like that?

72
00:08:22,168 --> 00:08:25,338
Well, I didn't know some coward
would muster up the courage

73
00:08:25,422 --> 00:08:27,972
and come running in opening the door wide.

74
00:08:28,925 --> 00:08:30,885
What a fool.

75
00:08:40,478 --> 00:08:42,108
What...

76
00:08:44,357 --> 00:08:45,357
Wait for me.

77
00:08:49,946 --> 00:08:50,986
A coward?

78
00:08:51,489 --> 00:08:54,079
Are you calling me a coward?

79
00:08:54,409 --> 00:08:55,739
There's no one else here.

80
00:08:55,869 --> 00:08:57,289
You're such a fool.

81
00:08:57,871 --> 00:09:00,001
What... A fool?

82
00:09:00,373 --> 00:09:02,253
Nobody ever called me that
in my whole life.

83
00:09:02,333 --> 00:09:05,053
-I have an MBA from Harvard, and world--
-Shut up!

84
00:09:06,796 --> 00:09:08,916
That's verbal violence.
Please rephrase it.

85
00:09:09,049 --> 00:09:10,549
-Okay. Shut it.
-Are you joking?

86
00:09:10,633 --> 00:09:12,643
-It's a ghost!
-Where?

87
00:09:12,719 --> 00:09:13,719
You are a coward.

88
00:09:16,598 --> 00:09:19,518
God... I thought there was really a ghost.

89
00:09:22,312 --> 00:09:25,942
I must've made a mistake
while burning the incense. I apologize.

90
00:09:26,524 --> 00:09:28,404
I'm glad you are safe.

91
00:09:32,197 --> 00:09:33,527
Yes.

92
00:09:33,615 --> 00:09:36,235
Ms. Choe, you should take
proper care of the rooms.

93
00:09:36,326 --> 00:09:39,286
That dangerous guest could've harmed
our manager.

94
00:09:44,876 --> 00:09:47,246
No, I'm sorry for worrying you.

95
00:09:55,678 --> 00:09:57,348
Do you see how I just improvised that?

96
00:09:58,223 --> 00:10:02,603
Mr. Third Choice has absolutely no idea
that we put him in that room on purpose.

97
00:10:02,685 --> 00:10:03,765
I don't know.

98
00:10:04,020 --> 00:10:05,900
You looked rather guilty.

99
00:10:06,606 --> 00:10:09,526
I think Mr. Koo is a fool
for not noticing that.

100
00:10:09,609 --> 00:10:12,529
Even if he is a fool, he will notice
when Ms. Fourth Choice comes.

101
00:10:12,612 --> 00:10:16,572
I should tell Hyeon-jung to postpone
bringing in Ms. Fourth Choice.

102
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:36,430
Yu-na, what are you doing?

103
00:10:37,554 --> 00:10:38,724
Get out of the way.

104
00:10:50,817 --> 00:10:52,487
-Did you just see Yu-na?
-Yes.

105
00:10:52,569 --> 00:10:54,779
I heard she's possessed
by Su-jeong's ghost.

106
00:10:54,946 --> 00:10:56,026
I think it's true.

107
00:10:56,114 --> 00:10:57,824
If you call out Su-jeong, she looks back.

108
00:10:57,907 --> 00:10:59,327
-Really?
-Really?

109
00:10:59,409 --> 00:11:00,829
-Let's go and see.
-Let's go.

110
00:11:00,910 --> 00:11:03,330
-You call her name.
-She really looks back?

111
00:11:03,413 --> 00:11:04,503
That's so weird.

112
00:11:07,375 --> 00:11:08,585
Su-jeong.

113
00:11:11,045 --> 00:11:12,045
It must be true.

114
00:11:12,130 --> 00:11:13,260
-That's so scary.
-It's scary.

115
00:11:13,339 --> 00:11:14,549
-What?
-What is this?

116
00:11:44,245 --> 00:11:45,285
Goodness.

117
00:11:45,580 --> 00:11:46,960
-What?
-What?

118
00:11:48,207 --> 00:11:50,127
-What's happening?
-What is that?

119
00:12:03,097 --> 00:12:04,097
What are you doing?

120
00:12:04,641 --> 00:12:06,311
I didn't want you to get hurt,
so I caught you.

121
00:12:06,476 --> 00:12:07,596
It can be painful.

122
00:12:07,685 --> 00:12:10,225
If I got hurt,
they would've looked at me as a human.

123
00:12:10,438 --> 00:12:12,018
Now, they will call me a monster.

124
00:12:16,152 --> 00:12:17,202
Hey.

125
00:12:18,112 --> 00:12:19,412
Wait for me.

126
00:12:19,781 --> 00:12:21,571
She's getting mad at me for helping her.

127
00:12:25,328 --> 00:12:27,538
You. How did you catch me?

128
00:12:28,539 --> 00:12:30,209
Ghosts can't catch humans.

129
00:12:30,333 --> 00:12:32,843
I'm not an average ghost.

130
00:12:38,549 --> 00:12:40,589
There are prayer beads and amulets
in here.

131
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:42,300
So get lost, you evil ghost.

132
00:12:42,512 --> 00:12:43,552
My friend.

133
00:12:43,680 --> 00:12:46,770
I'm not a ghost that can be
exorcised by power of religion.

134
00:12:46,849 --> 00:12:48,599
I have the right to stay in this world.

135
00:12:48,685 --> 00:12:51,395
I have a place I belong to,
and I also have a job.

136
00:12:52,063 --> 00:12:54,943
Don't make me laugh.
What kind of ghost has a job?

137
00:12:55,733 --> 00:12:58,153
I'm a hotelier. I'm from Hotel del Luna.

138
00:12:58,528 --> 00:12:59,488
Hotel del Luna?

139
00:12:59,570 --> 00:13:01,610
You know
the owner and manager of our hotel, right?

140
00:13:01,906 --> 00:13:04,116
They helped you live in that body.

141
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:05,030
So what?

142
00:13:05,159 --> 00:13:06,739
You want me to come out of this body?

143
00:13:07,829 --> 00:13:11,169
You are a really precious person.

144
00:13:11,332 --> 00:13:12,632
You're our precious hope.

145
00:13:14,711 --> 00:13:15,751
You are Ms. Fourth Choice.

146
00:13:16,004 --> 00:13:17,304
The fourth choice?

147
00:13:17,380 --> 00:13:19,630
You are the fourth choice
for our hotel's manager.

148
00:13:19,841 --> 00:13:22,301
Something has happened to
Mr. Third Choice,

149
00:13:22,385 --> 00:13:24,045
so I've come to take you,
the fourth choice.

150
00:13:24,137 --> 00:13:26,097
I don't know what you're talking about.

151
00:13:26,472 --> 00:13:28,472
But you are here because you need me.

152
00:13:28,558 --> 00:13:29,558
Yes.

153
00:13:32,895 --> 00:13:34,685
A ghost even has a mobile phone?

154
00:13:34,772 --> 00:13:37,942
Of course.
I have a job, so I also have a phone.

155
00:13:38,109 --> 00:13:39,689
I told you I have a right to stay here.

156
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:43,280
Your school's Wi-Fi is good.

157
00:13:44,073 --> 00:13:47,333
<i>Mr. Third Choice is unharmed.
Ms. Fourth Choice will be deferred.</i>

158
00:13:49,495 --> 00:13:51,865
Are you saying you don't need me?

159
00:13:51,956 --> 00:13:54,706
For now.
But I might be back to take you soon.

160
00:13:55,334 --> 00:13:56,504
So...

161
00:13:57,545 --> 00:13:59,165
keep studying hard at school.

162
00:14:02,300 --> 00:14:03,180
Hey!

163
00:14:08,598 --> 00:14:11,308
Give me your number.
I want to send texts to a ghost.

164
00:14:11,559 --> 00:14:14,189
I've never shared my number with a human.

165
00:14:16,647 --> 00:14:18,477
So you don't want to?

166
00:14:18,816 --> 00:14:19,776
You can't?

167
00:14:21,819 --> 00:14:22,819
Forget it then.

168
00:14:39,754 --> 00:14:41,174
<i>Okay. We're now friends.</i>

169
00:14:49,514 --> 00:14:51,684
The manager of Hotel del Luna?

170
00:14:52,558 --> 00:14:53,678
Sounds fun.

171
00:15:03,194 --> 00:15:04,204
Right.

172
00:15:04,821 --> 00:15:05,781
Wait...

173
00:15:05,863 --> 00:15:07,703
Mr. Ji?

174
00:15:08,449 --> 00:15:11,739
I'm glad to see you
still in your right mind.

175
00:15:13,287 --> 00:15:15,327
Thank you for being genuinely delighted.

176
00:15:17,625 --> 00:15:19,535
It sounds as if you all expected

177
00:15:19,627 --> 00:15:21,797
me to turn insane in that room.

178
00:15:21,879 --> 00:15:22,879
Gosh.

179
00:15:23,548 --> 00:15:25,378
You didn't, and that's all that matters.

180
00:15:33,558 --> 00:15:35,728
Ms. Fourth Choice is on standby.

181
00:15:35,810 --> 00:15:37,600
We also discussed

182
00:15:37,687 --> 00:15:40,187
a couple of other ways
to get rid of Mr. Third Choice.

183
00:15:41,732 --> 00:15:43,112
HOW TO ELIMINATE MR. THIRD CHOICE

184
00:15:43,192 --> 00:15:45,362
First, we can send him

185
00:15:45,445 --> 00:15:48,655
{\an8}to the ghost stationed
at the haunted house in Shincheon-gun.

186
00:15:55,663 --> 00:15:57,543
Thirty years is guaranteed

187
00:15:57,623 --> 00:15:59,583
if he stays clear
of the local Grim Reaper.

188
00:16:03,671 --> 00:16:06,421
Next, we can use a strong vengeful ghost

189
00:16:06,507 --> 00:16:08,127
to have him die suddenly.

190
00:16:08,217 --> 00:16:09,217
{\an8}VENGEFUL GHOST IN UIJEONGBU

191
00:16:10,636 --> 00:16:13,716
<i>He's an experienced killer
operating in Uijeongbu.</i>

192
00:16:13,806 --> 00:16:15,886
<i>Since he's close by, we can easily--</i>

193
00:16:15,975 --> 00:16:18,185
No, just drop it.

194
00:16:25,359 --> 00:16:26,609
Chan-sung isn't going anywhere.

195
00:16:27,195 --> 00:16:28,145
I'm keeping him by my side.

196
00:16:28,237 --> 00:16:30,737
What if the tree keeps transforming?

197
00:16:30,823 --> 00:16:33,413
Mago sent him here on purpose.

198
00:16:34,076 --> 00:16:35,406
You must drive him out.

199
00:16:37,163 --> 00:16:39,213
If he was really sent by a deity,

200
00:16:39,290 --> 00:16:42,250
then just chasing him out
won't solve anything.

201
00:16:42,335 --> 00:16:43,955
What if flowers blossom?

202
00:16:44,879 --> 00:16:45,879
Flowers?

203
00:16:47,882 --> 00:16:48,932
Let them blossom.

204
00:16:49,467 --> 00:16:51,257
Will there be a day

205
00:16:51,344 --> 00:16:55,224
when colorful flowers blossom and
I willingly walk across the Samdo River?

206
00:16:56,641 --> 00:16:58,141
We'll wait and see.

207
00:17:08,569 --> 00:17:12,069
Do you think she's had a change of heart
and is ready to go to the other world?

208
00:17:12,698 --> 00:17:15,538
No, I think she probably doesn't believe

209
00:17:15,743 --> 00:17:17,543
that flowers will really blossom.

210
00:17:17,620 --> 00:17:19,040
If that was the case,

211
00:17:19,121 --> 00:17:22,041
she shouldn't have agreed
to let him in Room 13.

212
00:17:22,667 --> 00:17:24,457
Her and her mood swings.

213
00:17:24,752 --> 00:17:28,802
I'm just glad that Mr. Koo
isn't the perceptive type.

214
00:17:30,007 --> 00:17:33,927
It'll be awkward if he figures out
that we led him there on purpose.

215
00:17:36,847 --> 00:17:38,887
You sent me to that room
on purpose, didn't you?

216
00:17:39,058 --> 00:17:40,478
You wanted me to die or lose my mind.

217
00:17:41,227 --> 00:17:43,557
You're not as dumb as I thought.
You're right.

218
00:17:43,813 --> 00:17:46,903
Everyone's disappointed
that you didn't go crazy.

219
00:17:50,695 --> 00:17:52,355
How can you all do this to me?

220
00:17:52,572 --> 00:17:55,742
I truly thought of you as my colleagues

221
00:17:55,950 --> 00:17:57,410
and started to like you guys.

222
00:17:57,994 --> 00:18:00,124
Isn't this considered as harassment?

223
00:18:00,204 --> 00:18:03,084
So? Are you here to tattle on them?

224
00:18:03,666 --> 00:18:05,036
Should I give them an earful?

225
00:18:05,126 --> 00:18:07,456
What's the point when you were in on it?

226
00:18:10,506 --> 00:18:13,506
You always ask questions
even though you know the answer.

227
00:18:13,884 --> 00:18:15,764
What a weirdo.

228
00:18:17,722 --> 00:18:18,762
Wait.

229
00:18:19,682 --> 00:18:20,812
Where did it go?

230
00:18:22,685 --> 00:18:23,595
Chan-sung,

231
00:18:24,228 --> 00:18:25,938
I lost one of the earrings.

232
00:18:26,272 --> 00:18:27,822
Check the floor for me.

233
00:18:28,482 --> 00:18:29,482
Seriously?

234
00:18:41,746 --> 00:18:43,116
Just let it slide.

235
00:18:43,289 --> 00:18:44,499
They're simply jealous

236
00:18:44,582 --> 00:18:46,672
because you're still alive
when they're not.

237
00:18:46,751 --> 00:18:48,461
How dumb do you think I am?

238
00:18:48,711 --> 00:18:50,131
What was this really about?

239
00:18:52,548 --> 00:18:54,628
The tree changed after you came here.

240
00:18:56,510 --> 00:18:59,260
We're worried
that our time to leave is near.

241
00:19:11,776 --> 00:19:13,276
Why did you save me though?

242
00:19:13,694 --> 00:19:15,454
If you hadn't, I would've gone crazy.

243
00:19:15,529 --> 00:19:17,239
I wasn't going to intervene,

244
00:19:17,740 --> 00:19:19,580
but a leaf changed my mind.

245
00:19:19,950 --> 00:19:20,950
A leaf?

246
00:19:25,081 --> 00:19:26,711
-This one?
-Yes.

247
00:19:26,791 --> 00:19:30,041
That small leaf bothered me.

248
00:19:33,589 --> 00:19:34,589
Are you saying,

249
00:19:35,633 --> 00:19:37,513
I won your heart by this much?

250
00:19:37,885 --> 00:19:39,425
You're doing it again!

251
00:19:39,970 --> 00:19:42,310
Asking questions
when you know the answer...

252
00:19:42,390 --> 00:19:44,100
Do they teach you that at Harvard?

253
00:19:44,183 --> 00:19:47,313
Asking questions to induce an answer
can lead to determining the truth.

254
00:19:47,395 --> 00:19:49,105
It's a known method by Socrates.

255
00:19:49,647 --> 00:19:51,517
That's what the professors
at Harvard taught me.

256
00:19:51,607 --> 00:19:54,857
But this isn't Harvard,
so just get back to finding my earring.

257
00:19:54,944 --> 00:19:57,614
Is finding it worth another leaf?

258
00:19:57,697 --> 00:19:58,657
Why you...

259
00:19:59,323 --> 00:20:00,993
Don't bother looking for it.

260
00:20:01,158 --> 00:20:03,038
If you find it, I'll kill you.

261
00:20:06,414 --> 00:20:09,424
You say you'll kill me,
but you don't mean it.

262
00:20:09,667 --> 00:20:11,747
You say you're not looking for it,
but you want to.

263
00:20:12,712 --> 00:20:15,592
I know you're cynical,
but your words are even more cynical.

264
00:20:15,923 --> 00:20:18,303
Is it because you've been living
as a ghost for too long?

265
00:20:18,384 --> 00:20:20,804
No, I was born this way.

266
00:20:20,886 --> 00:20:22,716
I've always been cynical.

267
00:20:22,805 --> 00:20:24,135
Did you not catch that in your dream?

268
00:20:24,890 --> 00:20:26,520
You were nice and kind.

269
00:20:26,600 --> 00:20:28,390
Me? Seriously?

270
00:20:28,519 --> 00:20:31,019
Yes, you cared for him with affection.

271
00:20:31,856 --> 00:20:35,226
His name was Yeon-u, I think.

272
00:20:44,243 --> 00:20:45,583
So you saw him too.

273
00:20:49,832 --> 00:20:50,832
I did.

274
00:20:53,502 --> 00:20:54,592
Yeon-u!

275
00:21:03,012 --> 00:21:04,932
You called his name with love,

276
00:21:05,973 --> 00:21:08,523
which is why it got stuck in my head.

277
00:21:10,019 --> 00:21:11,059
Why?

278
00:21:12,521 --> 00:21:14,271
Do you think you might be him?

279
00:21:16,025 --> 00:21:18,685
The thought crossed my mind,

280
00:21:19,445 --> 00:21:20,565
but it doesn't seem likely.

281
00:21:22,823 --> 00:21:23,873
Yeon-u was...

282
00:21:25,993 --> 00:21:28,703
the one who loved me the most.

283
00:21:31,332 --> 00:21:32,882
Do you love me too?

284
00:21:54,855 --> 00:21:56,145
I'm certain that I don't.

285
00:22:00,736 --> 00:22:01,736
Leave then.

286
00:22:40,776 --> 00:22:41,856
Yeon-u.

287
00:22:50,619 --> 00:22:51,619
<i>Man-wol.</i>

288
00:22:57,918 --> 00:22:59,548
With this tree you love,

289
00:23:00,004 --> 00:23:03,264
I'll build the biggest house
that anyone has ever seen.

290
00:23:03,340 --> 00:23:04,380
And you can have it.

291
00:23:05,426 --> 00:23:06,426
What?

292
00:23:07,094 --> 00:23:09,104
You'll build a house for me
with this tree?

293
00:23:10,222 --> 00:23:11,272
Forget it.

294
00:23:11,515 --> 00:23:13,555
I don't plan on building a house
and living with you.

295
00:23:14,351 --> 00:23:18,561
We all grow old.
You should think about putting down roots.

296
00:23:19,523 --> 00:23:22,573
I can't let you live under a tarp
when you become an old lady.

297
00:23:23,611 --> 00:23:27,071
I could be captured and killed
at any moment. That's my life.

298
00:23:28,157 --> 00:23:31,907
I don't even expect to live until I'm old.

299
00:23:31,994 --> 00:23:33,454
But you can.

300
00:23:34,496 --> 00:23:35,786
The fortune teller said

301
00:23:36,123 --> 00:23:38,793
that I'll live a long life
just like this tree.

302
00:23:39,585 --> 00:23:42,705
I'm expected to live 100 years,
so I'll give you my extra years.

303
00:23:43,714 --> 00:23:46,264
If you do, you'll die.

304
00:23:47,426 --> 00:23:48,426
You're right.

305
00:23:49,428 --> 00:23:50,508
It's okay, though.

306
00:23:51,263 --> 00:23:53,223
I don't mind dying for you,

307
00:23:53,724 --> 00:23:55,024
so you can have it all.

308
00:25:36,702 --> 00:25:39,332
This will find a human groom

309
00:25:39,413 --> 00:25:41,833
for your dead daughter.

310
00:25:58,056 --> 00:26:01,386
<i>Whoever finds the red pocket
that holds the deceased's desires</i>

311
00:26:01,477 --> 00:26:04,647
<i>shall be her soul's partner.</i>

312
00:26:08,692 --> 00:26:12,912
I hope that pocket will
find us a good man.

313
00:26:13,781 --> 00:26:15,121
Su-min.

314
00:26:15,866 --> 00:26:18,326
We're getting you married

315
00:26:18,410 --> 00:26:21,000
so that you don't get lonely.

316
00:26:24,792 --> 00:26:25,792
<i>No!</i>

317
00:26:26,210 --> 00:26:28,500
<i>I don't want to get married to a stranger.</i>

318
00:26:40,557 --> 00:26:42,767
You're getting off early today.

319
00:26:43,811 --> 00:26:45,521
Yes, I'm a bit tired.

320
00:26:45,604 --> 00:26:47,824
Well, you're the type
who makes more work for yourself.

321
00:26:47,981 --> 00:26:49,781
It is my job to tend to the guests

322
00:26:49,900 --> 00:26:51,360
as a hotelier.

323
00:26:51,443 --> 00:26:53,283
I guess you've changed your mindset.

324
00:26:53,570 --> 00:26:55,360
I thought you hated our hotel.

325
00:26:59,284 --> 00:27:00,414
Because I won...

326
00:27:01,286 --> 00:27:02,406
someone's heart.

327
00:27:03,747 --> 00:27:05,787
I'm actually a bit of a softie,

328
00:27:05,874 --> 00:27:07,634
so I repay favors by ten times the amount.

329
00:27:08,544 --> 00:27:10,844
-Sorry?
-That means if you're nice to me,

330
00:27:10,921 --> 00:27:12,511
I'll treat you really well.

331
00:27:13,006 --> 00:27:15,256
So please be nice to me.

332
00:27:21,974 --> 00:27:23,434
Did he figure anything out?

333
00:27:23,725 --> 00:27:24,725
What did he say?

334
00:27:25,185 --> 00:27:27,305
He used sarcasm to threaten me.

335
00:27:27,479 --> 00:27:30,689
He said he repays favors
by ten times the amount.

336
00:27:32,150 --> 00:27:35,200
I knew Mago wouldn't bring an easy one.

337
00:27:58,635 --> 00:28:00,135
Are you visiting the hotel, ma'am?

338
00:28:01,305 --> 00:28:02,635
Please help me.

339
00:28:07,477 --> 00:28:08,807
Are you all right, ma'am?

340
00:28:10,564 --> 00:28:12,444
You think this is the front desk?

341
00:28:13,400 --> 00:28:16,950
Why do you keep taking the guests
to my office instead of their rooms?

342
00:28:17,195 --> 00:28:18,315
She has her reasons.

343
00:28:18,405 --> 00:28:20,615
Every ghost has their reasons.

344
00:28:21,408 --> 00:28:23,738
And what's wrong with her? Is she drunk?

345
00:28:23,827 --> 00:28:26,077
She's exhausted
from roaming around too much.

346
00:28:27,789 --> 00:28:31,379
Ma'am, you can't do this to our employee.

347
00:28:31,460 --> 00:28:32,790
I am okay with it.

348
00:28:35,881 --> 00:28:38,301
Fine, then. Go ahead and hug her tight.

349
00:28:42,763 --> 00:28:45,683
She's being forced into a marriage.

350
00:28:45,766 --> 00:28:48,306
She doesn't want to get married
to a complete stranger,

351
00:28:48,685 --> 00:28:51,395
and she doesn't want
to get a living person possessed.

352
00:28:52,731 --> 00:28:54,571
{\an8}Is it a ghost wedding?

353
00:28:58,528 --> 00:29:02,198
It's for those who are still alive.
Why don't you just go along with it?

354
00:29:09,164 --> 00:29:12,424
You can go up to your room
and think it over again.

355
00:29:12,501 --> 00:29:14,501
Our hotel even has a wedding hall.

356
00:29:14,670 --> 00:29:17,340
If you pay the price,
we can even hold a party for you.

357
00:29:17,547 --> 00:29:19,757
Go ahead and think about it.

358
00:29:23,387 --> 00:29:24,757
Why don't you go up to your room?

359
00:29:36,608 --> 00:29:38,898
This won't do. Excuse me.

360
00:29:42,072 --> 00:29:43,162
Gosh.

361
00:29:52,791 --> 00:29:54,001
Chan-sung.

362
00:29:54,626 --> 00:29:57,796
I see you're strong enough to carry her.

363
00:29:58,380 --> 00:30:01,430
And you used a handcart meant for cabbages
to carry me.

364
00:30:09,766 --> 00:30:11,726
A ghost wedding...

365
00:30:27,826 --> 00:30:31,366
That guest was wearing
a Vera Wang wedding dress.

366
00:30:31,538 --> 00:30:33,498
That means she's from a rich family.

367
00:30:35,751 --> 00:30:38,381
-Get ready for the wedding.
-Yes, ma'am.

368
00:30:38,920 --> 00:30:41,670
Then I'll need to get a new dress.

369
00:30:42,341 --> 00:30:44,761
And I'll need new jewelry too.

370
00:30:44,843 --> 00:30:46,933
Shoes, a purse,

371
00:30:47,054 --> 00:30:48,314
and what else will I need?

372
00:30:49,139 --> 00:30:51,479
Gosh, there's so much to prepare.

373
00:30:53,518 --> 00:30:55,438
Chan-sung should

374
00:30:55,520 --> 00:30:59,520
hurry up and get that money
for the Baekdu Mountain painting.

375
00:31:35,727 --> 00:31:38,687
Good morning!

376
00:31:39,022 --> 00:31:40,612
Good morning, Sanchez.

377
00:31:40,816 --> 00:31:41,856
You're up?

378
00:31:42,234 --> 00:31:43,784
I guess you got some sleep last night.

379
00:31:44,069 --> 00:31:47,029
Yes, I slept well.
I didn't even dream this time.

380
00:31:48,573 --> 00:31:50,243
Maybe it was because I was tired.

381
00:31:50,409 --> 00:31:52,949
Did you buy a lottery ticket?
You want to have a lucky dream?

382
00:31:53,203 --> 00:31:56,253
No, I was expecting someone in my dreams.

383
00:31:56,498 --> 00:31:57,708
Your ex-girlfriend?

384
00:31:59,084 --> 00:32:02,254
The ex-boyfriend of a girl I know.

385
00:32:02,921 --> 00:32:04,381
Or her ex-boyfriends.

386
00:32:04,881 --> 00:32:08,011
It's not a dream,
but you missed a call from your friend.

387
00:32:08,135 --> 00:32:09,175
My friend?

388
00:32:10,137 --> 00:32:10,967
Who?

389
00:32:11,054 --> 00:32:12,014
Man-wol.

390
00:32:14,891 --> 00:32:15,731
Who?

391
00:32:15,809 --> 00:32:16,849
Man-wol, from your hotel.

392
00:32:16,935 --> 00:32:19,055
Your phone kept ringing,
so I just answered it.

393
00:32:19,187 --> 00:32:20,397
Man-wol

394
00:32:20,480 --> 00:32:23,110
told me to ask you
when you'd get the money for the painting.

395
00:32:24,025 --> 00:32:25,025
Sanchez,

396
00:32:25,694 --> 00:32:29,284
did you really call her by her name,
Man-wol?

397
00:32:29,531 --> 00:32:31,871
Didn't she get mad and yell at you?

398
00:32:32,576 --> 00:32:36,286
She agreed to call me by my name too.
Just Sanchez.

399
00:32:36,788 --> 00:32:38,748
We're even following each other
on our social media.

400
00:32:38,874 --> 00:32:41,334
You know what? She's actually

401
00:32:41,418 --> 00:32:44,498
quite friendly and polite. Right?

402
00:32:44,796 --> 00:32:46,466
Maybe it's because of her job?

403
00:32:48,592 --> 00:32:50,472
It seemed like she's used to being polite.

404
00:32:54,848 --> 00:32:58,938
She must have known
that Sanchez is really rich.

405
00:33:00,729 --> 00:33:02,399
That's why he was unharmed.

406
00:33:06,985 --> 00:33:08,065
"Man-wol"?

407
00:33:09,362 --> 00:33:10,912
-Put it right there.
-Yes, ma'am.

408
00:33:11,031 --> 00:33:13,951
Hyeon-jung, you said
you know how to play the piano, right?

409
00:33:14,242 --> 00:33:15,162
Practice.

410
00:33:15,368 --> 00:33:16,238
Yes, ma'am.

411
00:33:16,620 --> 00:33:18,960
It's been so long since we had a party.
I'm so excited.

412
00:33:19,039 --> 00:33:21,169
It's better to have many guests
for the party,

413
00:33:21,249 --> 00:33:23,879
so should I invite some guests
who are free?

414
00:33:24,586 --> 00:33:26,246
You think it'll look like a wedding

415
00:33:26,338 --> 00:33:29,088
if there are tons of ghosts in here?
It'll seem like a funeral.

416
00:33:29,841 --> 00:33:31,091
As few as possible.

417
00:33:31,760 --> 00:33:34,720
Yes, ma'am.
By the way, have we found the groom yet?

418
00:33:34,804 --> 00:33:37,724
If some unlucky human
finds that red pocket,

419
00:33:37,807 --> 00:33:39,137
he'll be the groom, I suppose.

420
00:33:39,267 --> 00:33:42,687
The bride doesn't seem to want
an arranged marriage like this.

421
00:33:42,771 --> 00:33:44,191
Mr. Koo went to find the red pocket,

422
00:33:44,272 --> 00:33:46,982
so he could return it to her parents
and talk them out of it.

423
00:33:47,484 --> 00:33:50,574
There won't be a wedding
if he finds it first, right?

424
00:33:54,741 --> 00:33:56,411
Chan-sung left to find the red pocket?

425
00:33:56,493 --> 00:33:59,793
Yes, he's very diligent,
so he's probably looking for it already.

426
00:34:00,121 --> 00:34:02,921
If he finds it, it'll cause trouble.

427
00:34:03,708 --> 00:34:04,748
Why?

428
00:34:08,129 --> 00:34:10,839
Will he become the groom

429
00:34:11,007 --> 00:34:12,797
if he finds it first?

430
00:34:13,385 --> 00:34:16,465
He's been caring so much about ghosts.
Now he's going to marry one.

431
00:34:16,555 --> 00:34:19,215
The bride didn't want to get married
to a complete stranger.

432
00:34:19,307 --> 00:34:21,887
But I bet she'll be okay
with marrying Mr. Koo.

433
00:34:21,977 --> 00:34:23,597
That's good news, Ms. Jang.

434
00:34:27,357 --> 00:34:30,147
Ms. Jang, are you going to let him
get married?

435
00:34:30,235 --> 00:34:31,275
Darn you!

436
00:34:52,507 --> 00:34:54,587
I heard the red pocket fell
somewhere near the lake.

437
00:35:02,100 --> 00:35:04,600
Chan-sung, you're still looking for it?

438
00:35:05,228 --> 00:35:08,108
What are you looking for?
I'll help you find it.

439
00:35:08,189 --> 00:35:09,359
No, it's okay.

440
00:35:09,774 --> 00:35:12,574
Don't mind me, and carry on.
You should ride another lap.

441
00:35:12,652 --> 00:35:14,152
It's going to rain soon.

442
00:35:14,946 --> 00:35:17,276
Then I'll go for one more lap.
Let's go home once I'm done.

443
00:35:17,365 --> 00:35:18,275
Okay.

444
00:35:44,142 --> 00:35:45,272
What are you doing here?

445
00:35:45,894 --> 00:35:47,064
Can't you see?

446
00:35:47,771 --> 00:35:48,981
I'm on a picnic.

447
00:35:49,064 --> 00:35:51,734
Why are you on a picnic? It's hot outside.

448
00:35:53,818 --> 00:35:54,898
Fine.

449
00:35:55,153 --> 00:35:58,623
Let me answer the question
that you already know the answer to.

450
00:35:58,698 --> 00:36:00,328
I'm here to see you.

451
00:36:00,742 --> 00:36:03,162
I don't want you to look
for that red pocket.

452
00:36:03,453 --> 00:36:04,453
Just leave it.

453
00:36:04,579 --> 00:36:07,169
Are you worried
I might have to marry her if I find it?

454
00:36:09,417 --> 00:36:11,917
Chan-sung, I'm against this marriage.

455
00:36:12,003 --> 00:36:13,463
I can't accept it.

456
00:36:14,631 --> 00:36:16,131
Just let some other guy pick it up.

457
00:36:16,383 --> 00:36:18,593
She doesn't want to marry
someone she doesn't know.

458
00:36:18,677 --> 00:36:21,177
Whoever picks it up
will get startled. If I find it,

459
00:36:21,262 --> 00:36:22,852
you'll take care of it for me.

460
00:36:24,849 --> 00:36:28,649
You think I'll have your back?
Is that why you're being reckless?

461
00:36:37,070 --> 00:36:38,360
Are you using that to find it?

462
00:36:40,115 --> 00:36:41,365
Can you see where it is?

463
00:36:46,287 --> 00:36:50,127
I see it.

464
00:36:53,586 --> 00:36:55,086
What's wrong with the bike?

465
00:37:14,107 --> 00:37:15,147
I found it.

466
00:37:16,484 --> 00:37:19,954
Chan-sung, you'll get to eat
at your friend's wedding.

467
00:37:30,123 --> 00:37:31,673
Sanchez!

468
00:37:51,978 --> 00:37:53,058
What is this?

469
00:38:03,156 --> 00:38:04,406
What the hell?

470
00:38:51,996 --> 00:38:53,076
Sanchez!

471
00:39:02,757 --> 00:39:03,717
Where is he?

472
00:39:23,570 --> 00:39:25,280
Sanchez, are you okay?

473
00:39:25,405 --> 00:39:28,405
I don't know if it's because of the rain,
but it's really cold.

474
00:39:29,284 --> 00:39:31,044
And maybe because of the rain,

475
00:39:31,119 --> 00:39:32,699
I saw something really weird.

476
00:39:34,372 --> 00:39:36,712
Chan-sung, I saw a strange woman

477
00:39:37,458 --> 00:39:39,128
in our house earlier.

478
00:39:39,294 --> 00:39:43,014
And I think she's still here.
I'm so scared.

479
00:39:43,172 --> 00:39:44,172
What should I do?

480
00:39:44,966 --> 00:39:46,006
Sanchez.

481
00:39:55,560 --> 00:39:57,400
You should go inside and get some sleep.

482
00:39:57,562 --> 00:39:58,942
Let me figure this out.

483
00:40:07,405 --> 00:40:08,405
Hello?

484
00:40:08,489 --> 00:40:11,329
<i>Are you Mr. Koo,
the manager at Hotel del Luna?</i>

485
00:40:13,244 --> 00:40:14,254
Yes, that's me.

486
00:40:14,329 --> 00:40:15,999
I got a call from that hotel

487
00:40:16,080 --> 00:40:18,540
saying they'd like to hold a wedding
for Su-min.

488
00:40:33,431 --> 00:40:36,271
Did you say you got a call
from the owner of our hotel?

489
00:40:37,769 --> 00:40:38,689
Yes.

490
00:40:42,523 --> 00:40:44,653
Are you here because of this?

491
00:40:52,575 --> 00:40:55,575
I didn't know
there was a hotel like this in Seoul.

492
00:41:00,416 --> 00:41:01,626
Welcome.

493
00:41:02,043 --> 00:41:05,173
I see that our manager
safely brought you here.

494
00:41:05,838 --> 00:41:10,888
Now, let's start discussing
the wedding in earnest.

495
00:41:13,096 --> 00:41:14,096
Come this way.

496
00:41:16,724 --> 00:41:19,564
This is where the wedding will take place.

497
00:41:19,686 --> 00:41:21,726
We can prepare a banquet

498
00:41:22,188 --> 00:41:25,438
and provide a suite for her
just like any other wedding.

499
00:41:25,692 --> 00:41:30,112
If you can do that, Su-min won't end up
dying a lonely soul.

500
00:41:30,196 --> 00:41:33,276
Please prepare the best of everything.

501
00:41:33,366 --> 00:41:35,026
We're doing this for our child.

502
00:41:35,118 --> 00:41:37,498
We'll pay and give you
anything that's necessary.

503
00:41:38,204 --> 00:41:41,544
By the way, who's the groom?

504
00:41:41,958 --> 00:41:45,038
You're forcing him to marry her
against his will.

505
00:41:45,378 --> 00:41:49,168
Don't you think you'd feel awkward
to meet the groom?

506
00:41:50,049 --> 00:41:52,259
Are you going to congratulate him
or something?

507
00:41:52,844 --> 00:41:55,054
Then I guess it'd be best not to meet him.

508
00:41:55,179 --> 00:41:57,059
We'll entrust you with everything.

509
00:41:57,640 --> 00:42:00,640
We'll do our best to prepare a wedding

510
00:42:01,227 --> 00:42:02,477
that will satisfy everyone.

511
00:42:11,362 --> 00:42:14,992
I knew they'd be rich.

512
00:42:15,116 --> 00:42:17,446
This is a black card that has no limit.

513
00:42:18,745 --> 00:42:22,325
Parents really have no limit
when it comes to loving their kids.

514
00:42:24,000 --> 00:42:25,590
This is my cup of tea.

515
00:42:29,589 --> 00:42:30,759
What are you planning to do?

516
00:42:32,508 --> 00:42:34,008
I'm going to prepare a wedding.

517
00:42:35,136 --> 00:42:37,056
Sanchez got really shocked.

518
00:42:37,138 --> 00:42:38,428
He's practically stupefied.

519
00:42:38,514 --> 00:42:41,064
It's because he's weak-hearted.

520
00:42:41,267 --> 00:42:44,647
That's why we should hold a wedding
and make her leave as soon as possible.

521
00:42:44,854 --> 00:42:48,154
Is Sanchez really going to be okay
once the wedding's over?

522
00:42:48,566 --> 00:42:50,186
Yes.

523
00:42:50,485 --> 00:42:52,485
It's not like they're going
to register their marriage.

524
00:42:52,779 --> 00:42:55,619
Just think of it as a short nightmare.

525
00:42:57,784 --> 00:43:00,544
There's so much to prepare.
We'll get so busy.

526
00:43:00,620 --> 00:43:02,370
Chan-sung, let's hurry.

527
00:43:08,086 --> 00:43:10,086
I wonder if this is
really going to be okay.

528
00:43:23,351 --> 00:43:25,521
God, I want to pee so bad.

529
00:43:25,603 --> 00:43:29,193
I'm about to burst,
but I'm too scared to go to the bathroom.

530
00:43:29,565 --> 00:43:31,225
When is Chan-sung coming home?

531
00:43:35,113 --> 00:43:37,663
Actually, no.

532
00:43:38,449 --> 00:43:40,789
It's okay. I can do it.

533
00:44:40,094 --> 00:44:41,724
So we were hurrying to go shopping?

534
00:44:41,804 --> 00:44:44,564
It's a wedding after all.
It should look sparkly.

535
00:44:56,435 --> 00:44:57,805
Are we here to buy wedding gifts?

536
00:44:58,520 --> 00:45:01,150
Are these necessary for this wedding?

537
00:45:01,231 --> 00:45:02,821
This one looks nice too.

538
00:45:03,692 --> 00:45:05,572
Why do we only have ten fingers?

539
00:45:05,652 --> 00:45:07,322
I wish I could put on more than ten.

540
00:45:08,655 --> 00:45:10,195
Are we here to buy your rings?

541
00:45:10,282 --> 00:45:12,122
You said we should hurry for Sanchez.

542
00:45:12,200 --> 00:45:14,120
This is no time to look at rings.

543
00:45:14,202 --> 00:45:16,502
I got my hands on a credit card
without a limit.

544
00:45:17,497 --> 00:45:20,577
If you're going to nag, go wait outside.

545
00:45:30,844 --> 00:45:33,684
I only have one neck,
so I can only wear one necklace.

546
00:45:33,805 --> 00:45:35,885
Wearing several necklaces
is becoming a thing.

547
00:45:36,600 --> 00:45:38,390
I like that.

548
00:45:38,852 --> 00:45:40,102
Bring me some more.

549
00:45:42,981 --> 00:45:46,491
Her parents didn't give you a credit card
to pay for your jewelry.

550
00:45:46,568 --> 00:45:47,988
It's meant to be used for the wedding.

551
00:45:48,070 --> 00:45:51,570
Exactly. I'm using their money
for the wedding.

552
00:45:51,907 --> 00:45:56,237
The more money I use for this wedding,

553
00:45:56,328 --> 00:45:58,038
the more relieved they will feel.

554
00:45:58,330 --> 00:46:00,920
Did you arrange the wedding
so you could do this?

555
00:46:00,999 --> 00:46:03,169
I'll return the credit card
and burn up the pocket.

556
00:46:03,251 --> 00:46:04,171
Go ahead.

557
00:46:04,252 --> 00:46:05,842
If you do that, your friend

558
00:46:05,921 --> 00:46:08,921
will have to live
the rest of his life with the ghost bride.

559
00:46:10,092 --> 00:46:12,722
The red pocket encompasses
a strong desire.

560
00:46:12,928 --> 00:46:14,848
That desire tied them together
with a red thread,

561
00:46:14,930 --> 00:46:16,430
so that they're forced to be together.

562
00:46:16,515 --> 00:46:17,965
If you burn the pocket,

563
00:46:18,058 --> 00:46:20,558
the bride will never get to go
to the afterlife.

564
00:46:21,937 --> 00:46:24,977
Can't you just cut their tie?

565
00:46:25,065 --> 00:46:27,645
I'm not the almighty.
Do you know how hard that is?

566
00:46:28,068 --> 00:46:31,658
We'll just have them get married,
then send the bride to the afterlife.

567
00:46:31,738 --> 00:46:33,658
That's what our hotel can do.

568
00:46:34,157 --> 00:46:36,157
Ma'am, please come to this side.

569
00:46:48,588 --> 00:46:51,338
PHARMACY
11-28 YAKJAE-GOLMOKGIL, GYEONGDONG MARKET

570
00:46:51,425 --> 00:46:58,055
HERB MEDICINE MARKET

571
00:47:03,520 --> 00:47:04,440
ORIENTAL HERBAL CLINIC

572
00:47:04,521 --> 00:47:05,521
HEALTH CARE CENTER

573
00:47:14,114 --> 00:47:17,534
PHARMACY

574
00:47:39,181 --> 00:47:40,061
Ma'am.

575
00:47:46,021 --> 00:47:47,401
You're really here.

576
00:47:50,942 --> 00:47:52,152
Who are you?

577
00:47:52,903 --> 00:47:53,903
I'm...

578
00:47:54,738 --> 00:47:56,528
I'm Koo Chan-sung from Hotel del Luna.

579
00:47:56,782 --> 00:48:00,042
You told me to come here to look for you
when we met on the subway.

580
00:48:06,166 --> 00:48:07,746
That wasn't me.

581
00:48:08,460 --> 00:48:10,130
That was my eldest sister.

582
00:48:11,254 --> 00:48:13,174
Hey!

583
00:48:13,256 --> 00:48:17,676
The weather outside is amazing!

584
00:48:19,262 --> 00:48:20,392
Who are you?

585
00:48:21,181 --> 00:48:24,811
He came from Hotel del Luna
to find our eldest sister.

586
00:48:25,769 --> 00:48:27,479
Hotel del Luna?

587
00:48:27,562 --> 00:48:30,272
Our sister goes there often
to pick flowers, doesn't she?

588
00:48:31,358 --> 00:48:33,238
Are you twins?

589
00:48:33,485 --> 00:48:35,945
I mean, triplets?

590
00:48:38,532 --> 00:48:41,082
There are more than three of us.

591
00:48:41,868 --> 00:48:46,208
Why are you asking for our sister anyway?

592
00:48:53,380 --> 00:48:56,340
There will be a ghost wedding
at Hotel del Luna?

593
00:48:56,424 --> 00:48:59,554
The bride doesn't want a wedding
she never asked for,

594
00:48:59,636 --> 00:49:01,426
and the groom is shivering in fear.

595
00:49:01,638 --> 00:49:02,848
Is there a way to fix this?

596
00:49:04,140 --> 00:49:06,520
Like what your boss said,

597
00:49:06,601 --> 00:49:08,651
it'd be best to do the wedding

598
00:49:08,728 --> 00:49:11,818
for the sake of those who are alive.

599
00:49:12,774 --> 00:49:15,574
I guess we don't have a choice
but to hold the wedding.

600
00:49:16,111 --> 00:49:19,111
I know! We could switch the groom.

601
00:49:19,322 --> 00:49:20,782
Instead of someone living,

602
00:49:20,866 --> 00:49:24,196
you could find someone dead as her groom.

603
00:49:25,579 --> 00:49:27,829
Where are we going to find a dead groom?

604
00:49:27,914 --> 00:49:31,674
You have a lot of guests at your hotel.

605
00:49:32,502 --> 00:49:33,552
You're right.

606
00:49:33,628 --> 00:49:34,708
Right?

607
00:49:35,755 --> 00:49:38,875
The bride can choose a groom she likes

608
00:49:38,967 --> 00:49:41,137
to give the red pocket.

609
00:49:41,219 --> 00:49:43,969
The two ghosts can get together

610
00:49:44,055 --> 00:49:47,135
and head over to the afterlife,
holding hands.

611
00:49:47,225 --> 00:49:49,225
Yes, I'll try that.

612
00:49:49,311 --> 00:49:51,151
Thank you. I'll get going.

613
00:49:57,235 --> 00:49:58,275
Hey.

614
00:49:59,154 --> 00:50:01,324
You must be tired from working at night.

615
00:50:02,032 --> 00:50:03,662
You probably can't sleep well.

616
00:50:04,326 --> 00:50:07,286
Try this one. I'm sure it'll help.

617
00:50:13,251 --> 00:50:14,591
It's herb tonic tea.

618
00:50:14,711 --> 00:50:15,841
Thank you.

619
00:50:22,802 --> 00:50:26,682
I think she likes you.

620
00:50:26,806 --> 00:50:29,306
That's precious medicine.

621
00:50:29,601 --> 00:50:33,481
You'll feel energetic
even from a short nap.

622
00:50:33,563 --> 00:50:34,733
Really?

623
00:50:36,316 --> 00:50:37,316
Thank you.

624
00:50:41,488 --> 00:50:42,528
Great.

625
00:50:43,031 --> 00:50:45,871
I narrowed it down to guests
who died before getting married.

626
00:50:45,951 --> 00:50:46,991
Okay.

627
00:50:47,619 --> 00:50:50,749
I better visit them one by one
to ask if they're interested.

628
00:50:50,914 --> 00:50:52,674
Let's start with Room 507.

629
00:50:59,005 --> 00:51:00,505
I'm sorry to interrupt.

630
00:51:01,299 --> 00:51:04,139
But are you interested
in going on a blind date?

631
00:51:07,389 --> 00:51:10,269
We'll now start the date
between Ms. Lee Su-min

632
00:51:10,350 --> 00:51:11,980
and her five prospect grooms.

633
00:51:16,523 --> 00:51:17,863
Why are you sitting there?

634
00:51:17,941 --> 00:51:19,861
Because I want to get married too.

635
00:51:19,943 --> 00:51:21,953
Employees can't participate.
Get back here.

636
00:51:22,028 --> 00:51:22,948
What?

637
00:51:23,029 --> 00:51:24,069
Get over here.

638
00:51:24,447 --> 00:51:25,447
What?

639
00:51:25,949 --> 00:51:28,699
I even got changed for this.
This is unfair.

640
00:51:28,785 --> 00:51:30,825
We'll start over again.

641
00:51:30,954 --> 00:51:33,254
Due to the time limit,
we'll make it short.

642
00:51:33,915 --> 00:51:35,995
Please greet each other
while the hourglass is running.

643
00:51:36,084 --> 00:51:37,884
Tell her about what you did
when you were alive.

644
00:51:37,961 --> 00:51:41,011
I hope you'll get to have
sincere conversations.

645
00:51:50,348 --> 00:51:55,098
Gosh, Chan-sung is wasting his time again.

646
00:51:58,481 --> 00:52:01,651
At least,
the bride will get to marry a groom

647
00:52:01,735 --> 00:52:03,775
whom she can connect better with.

648
00:52:04,029 --> 00:52:07,369
I don't know. I doubt there will be
a man the bride likes.

649
00:52:11,995 --> 00:52:13,615
I like this one.

650
00:52:20,587 --> 00:52:21,707
As you might have noticed,

651
00:52:21,796 --> 00:52:24,216
my friend has a weak heart
and won't be able to do the wedding.

652
00:52:26,593 --> 00:52:29,473
You should choose one of them
to leave for the afterlife together.

653
00:52:29,554 --> 00:52:31,264
It's the best I can do for you.

654
00:52:41,524 --> 00:52:43,444
Please make sure to keep time, everyone.

655
00:52:43,526 --> 00:52:45,566
We'll start with the table number one.

656
00:52:45,820 --> 00:52:49,450
Please give the red pocket
to the person you like.

657
00:52:50,492 --> 00:52:51,582
Let's begin.

658
00:53:33,076 --> 00:53:34,116
Please take it.

659
00:53:35,036 --> 00:53:37,536
If I have a wedding with one of them,
I must go with him.

660
00:53:37,622 --> 00:53:39,212
I want to go alone.

661
00:53:39,874 --> 00:53:42,714
I want you, a human, to take it
so I can do that.

662
00:53:44,754 --> 00:53:45,764
But...

663
00:53:48,133 --> 00:53:50,183
If you won't,
I'll just stick to the original plan.

664
00:53:50,343 --> 00:53:52,303
Please bring your friend.

665
00:54:21,583 --> 00:54:22,583
What?

666
00:54:23,668 --> 00:54:25,878
Who did she pick as her husband again?

667
00:54:25,962 --> 00:54:27,962
She said she wants
to have a wedding with Mr. Koo.

668
00:54:28,047 --> 00:54:30,587
Mr. Koo accepted it,
so they are getting ready now.

669
00:54:35,305 --> 00:54:36,805
Will you be the officiant?

670
00:54:36,890 --> 00:54:37,890
Hyeon-jung,

671
00:54:37,974 --> 00:54:40,314
go to Ms. Fourth Choice right now.

672
00:54:40,560 --> 00:54:41,520
Why?

673
00:54:43,688 --> 00:54:45,438
Are you going to send Mr. Koo

674
00:54:46,024 --> 00:54:48,234
to the afterlife together with the bride?

675
00:55:04,918 --> 00:55:06,878
I don't even know what I'm doing now.

676
00:55:11,674 --> 00:55:12,514
Okay.

677
00:55:13,134 --> 00:55:14,644
Let's just think this is a dream.

678
00:55:15,345 --> 00:55:16,755
This is just a meaningless dream.

679
00:55:16,846 --> 00:55:18,886
Everything will be gone once I wake up.

680
00:55:33,446 --> 00:55:34,446
All right.

681
00:55:36,032 --> 00:55:37,952
I'm just going to have a short dream.

682
00:56:46,060 --> 00:56:49,440
Ms. Jang, are you getting married?

683
00:56:50,898 --> 00:56:51,978
What?

684
00:56:52,525 --> 00:56:54,315
Aren't you the one getting married?

685
00:56:55,236 --> 00:56:57,156
GROOM'S ROOM

686
00:57:02,327 --> 00:57:04,697
I guess I had a dream just now.

687
00:57:04,787 --> 00:57:05,827
Chan-sung.

688
00:57:05,913 --> 00:57:08,583
How dare you decide to get married
without my permission?

689
00:57:08,666 --> 00:57:11,376
Why do I need your permission
when I'm the one getting married?

690
00:57:11,753 --> 00:57:15,093
So are you really going to marry her?

691
00:57:15,256 --> 00:57:17,626
This is why you should have helped her
when she came to you,

692
00:57:17,717 --> 00:57:19,387
saying she didn't want to get married.

693
00:57:22,263 --> 00:57:24,223
Do you think she doesn't
want to get married?

694
00:57:24,849 --> 00:57:28,599
No way. She's a ghost
that is mad about getting married.

695
00:57:33,399 --> 00:57:35,569
The strong desires sealed here

696
00:57:35,652 --> 00:57:37,532
belong to that woman who will never leave

697
00:57:37,612 --> 00:57:38,862
before she gets married.

698
00:57:55,713 --> 00:57:58,883
What a beautiful bride.

699
00:58:01,886 --> 00:58:06,466
I heard there's a wedding
at Hotel del Luna, and I came by.

700
00:58:10,436 --> 00:58:14,976
This is my wedding gift for the bride.

701
00:58:23,324 --> 00:58:28,084
You get married to become happy.

702
00:58:35,336 --> 00:58:36,336
Chan-sung.

703
00:58:38,214 --> 00:58:40,224
I'll save you again.

704
00:58:40,550 --> 00:58:42,220
You don't have to have
the unwanted wedding.

705
00:58:43,010 --> 00:58:45,890
Then what do I do with this?
You said this can't be removed.

706
00:58:46,472 --> 00:58:49,102
We should let her
have a wedding as she wishes.

707
00:58:49,892 --> 00:58:53,402
I'm going to bring her real groom
whom she can never...

708
00:58:54,897 --> 00:58:56,147
leave behind.

709
00:59:10,830 --> 00:59:12,370
This lady is your girlfriend, right?

710
00:59:17,295 --> 00:59:19,955
Your girlfriend is marrying
some other guy.

711
00:59:20,590 --> 00:59:22,720
Hey, that's not funny.

712
00:59:23,384 --> 00:59:25,724
I'm not kidding.
If you want to stop the wedding,

713
00:59:25,803 --> 00:59:27,603
you need to go marry her.

714
00:59:49,619 --> 00:59:52,249
The groom that you actually want to marry,

715
00:59:53,080 --> 00:59:54,290
I brought him here.

716
00:59:57,210 --> 01:00:00,380
We have such a great customer service,
don't we?

717
01:00:01,547 --> 01:00:03,377
It looks like you can finally marry

718
01:00:04,258 --> 01:00:06,508
the person you never got over
even after you died.

719
01:00:09,263 --> 01:00:10,433
You must be

720
01:00:11,182 --> 01:00:12,772
very happy.

721
01:00:18,940 --> 01:00:20,270
He should be here any minute now.

722
01:01:19,750 --> 01:01:20,920
Su-min.

723
01:02:34,575 --> 01:02:36,325
<i>When the wedding is over,</i>

724
01:02:37,411 --> 01:02:39,081
<i>the man will die.</i>

725
01:02:48,506 --> 01:02:51,876
The bride will take her man
to the afterlife with her.

726
01:02:55,638 --> 01:02:58,058
I wonder if Chan-sung noticed.

727
01:03:15,908 --> 01:03:20,578
That's why the man's parents
tried to marry her off to anyone

728
01:03:20,997 --> 01:03:22,497
through a ghost wedding.

729
01:03:23,290 --> 01:03:26,210
<i>The man's parents?
They weren't the bride's parents?</i>

730
01:03:27,336 --> 01:03:29,706
It was the man's parents
who requested to hold the wedding.

731
01:03:30,089 --> 01:03:33,629
They were afraid the woman
would take their son with her.

732
01:03:39,223 --> 01:03:41,063
Su-min is dead.

733
01:03:41,600 --> 01:03:43,770
I can't let you go with her.

734
01:03:54,613 --> 01:03:57,623
Why doesn't it come off?

735
01:03:58,784 --> 01:04:02,664
Su-min, please let my son go. Please...

736
01:04:03,456 --> 01:04:05,496
Please let him go!

737
01:04:36,197 --> 01:04:38,737
Ms. Lee, stop. You shouldn't do this.

738
01:04:58,636 --> 01:05:00,216
Let's be together forever.

739
01:05:13,442 --> 01:05:16,112
Ms. Lee, he's still alive.

740
01:05:16,195 --> 01:05:17,485
Stop right now!

741
01:05:19,698 --> 01:05:20,738
Ms. Lee!

742
01:05:44,723 --> 01:05:45,773
No.

743
01:05:50,187 --> 01:05:51,437
We must stop.

744
01:05:53,107 --> 01:05:54,107
Go back.

745
01:05:55,568 --> 01:05:56,778
What's the matter, Su-min?

746
01:05:57,945 --> 01:05:59,195
Go!

747
01:06:07,204 --> 01:06:08,084
Su-min.

748
01:07:42,675 --> 01:07:44,465
<i>It's hard,</i>

749
01:07:44,551 --> 01:07:48,311
<i>but sometimes it's easier
to let go than hold on.</i>

750
01:08:49,575 --> 01:08:50,695
I love you.

751
01:08:53,620 --> 01:08:55,040
Please be happy.

752
01:10:07,236 --> 01:10:09,656
This place looks cooler than I imagined.

753
01:10:09,738 --> 01:10:11,368
I'll start working
as the manager right away.

754
01:10:11,448 --> 01:10:13,778
You can't yet. We have Mr. Koo.

755
01:10:13,867 --> 01:10:15,407
Then I'll be the intern for now.

756
01:10:15,828 --> 01:10:17,498
Let me start training as an intern.

757
01:10:19,581 --> 01:10:20,501
Listen, friend.

758
01:10:20,791 --> 01:10:22,581
It's getting late.

759
01:10:22,876 --> 01:10:26,546
You should go home to sleep
so you can go to school tomorrow.

760
01:10:27,881 --> 01:10:28,881
Hey.

761
01:10:29,633 --> 01:10:30,723
Hey.

762
01:10:41,437 --> 01:10:43,647
I'm sorry I used you in such a vulgar way.

763
01:10:44,022 --> 01:10:46,442
I'm sure you haven't survived
since the Tang Dynasty

764
01:10:46,525 --> 01:10:47,525
to be used that way.

765
01:11:49,838 --> 01:11:50,918
Mi-ra.

766
01:11:52,466 --> 01:11:55,676
It's been a while.
I'm here to see Chan-sung.

767
01:12:02,476 --> 01:12:05,476
Thank you for helping me
cut the tie before I leave.

768
01:12:05,729 --> 01:12:07,769
I hope your journey will be comfortable.

769
01:12:14,821 --> 01:12:17,321
Those scissors are
from the third crone, right?

770
01:12:18,784 --> 01:12:20,914
Did she come to my hotel
without me knowing?

771
01:12:21,203 --> 01:12:23,463
He's the one who went to see Mago.

772
01:12:25,207 --> 01:12:27,787
Now the crones are all helping
Chan-sung together?

773
01:12:27,876 --> 01:12:30,246
You're the one that Mago is helping.

774
01:12:32,297 --> 01:12:35,877
He'll be the one to see you off.

775
01:13:48,457 --> 01:13:52,497
I felt proud to see my guests off
at my previous hotel,

776
01:13:54,546 --> 01:13:55,956
but I feel lonely here.

777
01:13:57,716 --> 01:13:59,716
That's because you won't ever see them
again.

778
01:14:03,221 --> 01:14:04,221
Chan-sung.

779
01:14:05,557 --> 01:14:07,097
You're doing a good job.

780
01:14:08,685 --> 01:14:10,395
Mago was right about you.

781
01:14:11,021 --> 01:14:12,231
I get why she likes you.

782
01:14:13,607 --> 01:14:15,317
Did you know I met with her?

783
01:14:20,864 --> 01:14:22,874
She told me to take good care of you,

784
01:14:24,076 --> 01:14:25,286
so that leaves will grow

785
01:14:26,078 --> 01:14:27,368
and flowers will bloom.

786
01:14:31,750 --> 01:14:32,790
You...

787
01:14:34,378 --> 01:14:36,378
Do you still see me in your dreams?

788
01:14:57,401 --> 01:14:58,401
Yes.

789
01:15:02,739 --> 01:15:05,029
I hope you keep it up
and take good care of me

790
01:15:06,159 --> 01:15:07,289
and then...

791
01:15:08,620 --> 01:15:09,790
see me off.

792
01:15:10,747 --> 01:15:12,117
That's what Mago wants.

793
01:15:19,089 --> 01:15:21,299
I'll become your last guest

794
01:15:22,134 --> 01:15:24,344
because you are my cup of tea.

795
01:15:34,896 --> 01:15:35,896
Chan-sung.

796
01:15:39,192 --> 01:15:40,492
When you see me off,

797
01:15:43,071 --> 01:15:44,321
don't feel lonely.

798
01:16:48,970 --> 01:16:50,470
{\an8}He's not answering his phone.

799
01:16:50,722 --> 01:16:51,562
{\an8}What did you say?

800
01:16:51,640 --> 01:16:53,480
{\an8}Your Majesty!

801
01:16:53,558 --> 01:16:55,308
{\an8}<i>He's dressed like a king of Joseon.</i>

802
01:16:55,393 --> 01:16:56,603
{\an8}<i>Which one is he?</i>

803
01:16:57,479 --> 01:16:58,649
{\an8}I'm really worried about you.

804
01:16:58,730 --> 01:16:59,900
{\an8}<i>Why are you doing this to me?</i>

805
01:16:59,981 --> 01:17:02,111
{\an8}Because I cannot have you reincarnated
as a dog or a pig.

806
01:17:02,192 --> 01:17:03,692
{\an8}You could get kicked out at this rate--

807
01:17:03,944 --> 01:17:04,954
{\an8}You're doing a great job.

808
01:17:05,028 --> 01:17:06,908
{\an8}One, two, three, we can do it!

809
01:17:07,197 --> 01:17:08,407
{\an8}<i>I hate being poor.</i>

810
01:17:08,490 --> 01:17:10,910
{\an8}I'm going to keep eating
caviar and champagne.

811
01:17:10,992 --> 01:17:12,082
{\an8}<i>He has a girlfriend?</i>

812
01:17:12,160 --> 01:17:13,790
{\an8}-I have her picture.
-Forget it. Don't tell me.

813
01:17:13,870 --> 01:17:15,330
{\an8}Why are you telling me that?

814
01:17:15,413 --> 01:17:16,543
{\an8}<i>Is she pretty?</i>

815
01:17:17,666 --> 01:17:19,666
{\an8}Subtitle translation by Wayne Ryu

816
01:17:39,802 --> 01:17:41,052
Chan-sung.

817
01:17:41,553 --> 01:17:42,893
When you see me off,

818
01:17:45,474 --> 01:17:46,684
don't feel lonely.

819
01:17:48,435 --> 01:17:50,645
I hope you keep it up
and take good care of me

820
01:17:51,438 --> 01:17:52,688
and then...

821
01:17:53,232 --> 01:17:54,282
see me off.

822
01:17:55,401 --> 01:17:56,691
That's what Mago wants.

823
01:18:01,532 --> 01:18:02,452
What are you doing?

824
01:18:04,827 --> 01:18:05,827
What?

825
01:18:08,664 --> 01:18:10,004
Do you want me to go right now?

826
01:18:17,214 --> 01:18:19,594
Don't rush it. Now isn't the right time.

827
01:18:20,175 --> 01:18:23,345
Do you really think
I'll leave that easily?

828
01:18:24,263 --> 01:18:28,183
I'll make you feel miserable
and get sick and tired of me.

829
01:18:28,642 --> 01:18:29,942
When I leave,

830
01:18:30,311 --> 01:18:33,561
you'll probably put on a big smile
and feel extremely relieved.

831
01:19:29,787 --> 01:19:30,867
Sir.

832
01:19:31,455 --> 01:19:33,035
You shouldn't be here.

833
01:19:36,335 --> 01:19:37,205
Sir.

834
01:19:37,711 --> 01:19:39,961
I know you can see me.
You can hear me, right?

835
01:19:40,047 --> 01:19:41,797
Damn it!

836
01:19:44,468 --> 01:19:45,968
Please don't spit on me.

837
01:19:47,221 --> 01:19:48,351
Stop it.

838
01:19:48,764 --> 01:19:50,774
How drunk is he?

839
01:19:50,849 --> 01:19:52,229
I don't think he's drunk.

840
01:19:52,309 --> 01:19:53,769
-I think he's just crazy.
-Sir!

841
01:19:53,852 --> 01:19:56,652
-My goodness.
-There are so many weird people.

842
01:19:56,730 --> 01:20:00,030
Calm down and follow me.

843
01:20:00,484 --> 01:20:02,244
-My gosh.
-Poor thing.

844
01:20:02,319 --> 01:20:05,199
Hey, be quiet. Let's not provoke him.

845
01:20:10,953 --> 01:20:13,083
I bought you beer like I promised.

846
01:20:13,455 --> 01:20:14,745
Thank you.

847
01:20:15,457 --> 01:20:18,167
Go to the hotel I told you about
once you're done with the beer.

848
01:20:19,002 --> 01:20:21,052
You'll be able to find it
if you follow the moon.

849
01:20:22,005 --> 01:20:23,045
Okay.

850
01:20:26,051 --> 01:20:28,011
-I can't believe this.
-This is so cool.

851
01:20:28,679 --> 01:20:31,099
-My gosh, look at him.
-Kim Jun-hyun?

852
01:20:33,809 --> 01:20:35,389
It's a sausage.

853
01:20:37,229 --> 01:20:38,479
Welcome.

854
01:20:41,567 --> 01:20:42,607
That's 1,800 won.

855
01:20:42,693 --> 01:20:44,453
-It's really him.
-He's really fat.

856
01:20:44,528 --> 01:20:46,818
I'm a fan of yours.
Are you shooting something nearby?

857
01:20:47,322 --> 01:20:49,742
I really like it when you take
those huge one bites on your show.

858
01:20:50,242 --> 01:20:51,872
-I can't believe it's him.
-Gosh, look.

859
01:20:51,952 --> 01:20:53,002
-He's coming.
-He's coming.

860
01:20:53,078 --> 01:20:54,958
-Hello.
-Hi.

861
01:20:55,038 --> 01:20:58,168
-I'm a huge fan.
-Thank you.

862
01:20:58,584 --> 01:21:00,674
Can I please get an autograph?

863
01:21:01,420 --> 01:21:04,090
-Now is not the time to follow...
-This is so cool.

864
01:21:07,551 --> 01:21:10,261
I can't believe
he's even popular among ghosts.

865
01:21:11,722 --> 01:21:14,022
This restaurant was
on The Guys Who Died After Eating.

866
01:21:14,099 --> 01:21:15,519
Kim Jun-hyun...

867
01:21:15,726 --> 01:21:18,436
He ate five balls of sticky rice cake
at once.

868
01:21:19,062 --> 01:21:21,772
That guy. He's not an ordinary man.

869
01:21:26,028 --> 01:21:27,738
Jang Man-wol likes him too.

870
01:21:32,659 --> 01:21:34,699
-I got the leg.
-You need to put that in.

871
01:21:34,786 --> 01:21:36,206
-Yes.
-My goodness.

872
01:21:36,622 --> 01:21:38,752
You're only going to have
the webfoot octopus?

873
01:21:38,832 --> 01:21:39,832
Yes.

874
01:21:40,459 --> 01:21:43,209
Ms. Fourth Choice came by today,
and she's very clever.

875
01:21:43,712 --> 01:21:46,132
She volunteered to intern here.

876
01:21:46,423 --> 01:21:47,633
Why don't we let her do that?

877
01:21:48,550 --> 01:21:50,180
Let her do what she wants.

878
01:21:50,260 --> 01:21:54,010
Then I'll put Hyeon-jung
in charge of training her.

879
01:21:54,181 --> 01:21:56,731
I'll make sure he teaches her well
so she can take over right away

880
01:21:57,017 --> 01:21:58,187
as soon as Mr. Koo quits.

881
01:21:58,268 --> 01:22:00,478
By the way, did Chan-sung leave?

882
01:22:00,729 --> 01:22:02,939
Yes, he took the afternoon off today

883
01:22:03,023 --> 01:22:04,783
and went home early.

884
01:22:05,943 --> 01:22:07,073
One bite!

885
01:22:08,237 --> 01:22:11,777
KIM JUN-HYUN ATTEMPTS TO EAT
EVERYTHING IN ONE BITE

886
01:22:13,659 --> 01:22:15,829
Are you craving that food?

887
01:22:17,788 --> 01:22:20,118
Should I have the intern go buy some?

888
01:22:21,250 --> 01:22:22,250
No.

889
01:22:23,377 --> 01:22:25,377
I don't really crave anything today.

890
01:22:38,183 --> 01:22:39,183
Did you

891
01:22:39,851 --> 01:22:41,691
find this?

892
01:22:45,816 --> 01:22:46,816
No.

893
01:22:48,610 --> 01:22:50,240
I thought I lost it.

894
01:22:52,572 --> 01:22:55,452
Is finding it worth another leaf?

895
01:22:59,329 --> 01:23:01,209
If I want to show him these,

896
01:23:01,915 --> 01:23:04,125
I should start craving
the webfoot octopus.

897
01:23:16,263 --> 01:23:17,973
Hello? Hey, Man-wol.

898
01:23:18,765 --> 01:23:20,515
Chan-sung? He's not home yet.

899
01:23:20,934 --> 01:23:22,564
He's not answering his phone.

900
01:23:22,686 --> 01:23:26,766
Once he comes home, tell him to wait
for me. Tell him I'll be picking him up

901
01:23:26,898 --> 01:23:28,278
in my poop colored car.

902
01:23:28,358 --> 01:23:31,148
Man-wol, Chan-sung
might come home late tonight.

903
01:23:31,320 --> 01:23:32,740
What? Why?

904
01:23:32,821 --> 01:23:34,491
His girlfriend came by today.

905
01:23:39,661 --> 01:23:40,661
What did you just say?

906
01:23:40,746 --> 01:23:43,246
She's the girl he used to date
back when he was in the States.

907
01:23:43,332 --> 01:23:45,212
She came to my house to meet Chan-sung.

908
01:23:45,625 --> 01:23:47,165
But they must be meeting outside.

909
01:23:48,128 --> 01:23:49,338
My gosh, you startled me.

910
01:23:50,088 --> 01:23:51,378
Are you already here?

911
01:23:53,800 --> 01:23:56,800
Chan-sung has a girlfriend?

912
01:23:58,764 --> 01:24:00,894
Who is she? Is she pretty?

913
01:24:01,767 --> 01:24:03,597
-Well--
-Forget it. Don't tell me.

914
01:24:04,519 --> 01:24:07,149
Why are you telling me that?
I never said I was curious.

915
01:24:07,230 --> 01:24:09,440
I'm not interested. At all.

916
01:24:10,817 --> 01:24:13,027
-See you.
-But I haven't said anything yet.

917
01:24:13,111 --> 01:24:15,861
If you want to tell me so badly, go ahead.
I'll hear you out.

918
01:24:18,700 --> 01:24:19,870
Is she pretty?

919
01:24:23,121 --> 01:24:24,541
I just asked if she's pretty.

920
01:24:26,667 --> 01:24:29,537
Yes, she's pretty. She's pretty.

921
01:24:33,465 --> 01:24:34,625
Sanchez.

922
01:24:35,842 --> 01:24:39,642
You really are slow-witted.

923
01:24:41,473 --> 01:24:44,433
You know nothing, do you?

924
01:24:44,976 --> 01:24:46,516
You're so stupid.

925
01:24:48,271 --> 01:24:49,481
Is she...

926
01:24:50,482 --> 01:24:51,692
that pretty?

927
01:24:57,114 --> 01:25:00,454
Yes, she's really pretty. She's smart too.

928
01:25:00,534 --> 01:25:02,124
And she and Chan-sung make a great couple.

929
01:25:02,202 --> 01:25:04,752
I have her picture. You want to see it?
I'll go find it. Wait here.

930
01:25:08,917 --> 01:25:11,377
If she really turns out to be pretty,

931
01:25:12,713 --> 01:25:15,423
I'll kill you, Sanchez.

932
01:25:22,806 --> 01:25:24,016
Man-wol, look.

933
01:25:26,184 --> 01:25:28,354
Man-wol? Did she leave?

934
01:25:31,815 --> 01:25:34,105
I wonder if Chan-sung's late
because he met Mi-ra.

935
01:25:43,368 --> 01:25:47,368
Their connection has lasted
for a very long time.

936
01:25:55,672 --> 01:25:58,012
I hope he takes good care of her,

937
01:25:59,718 --> 01:26:02,638
so that she doesn't end up
getting hurt again.

938
01:26:15,484 --> 01:26:16,904
-Unbelievable.
-This is incredible.

939
01:26:17,110 --> 01:26:18,900
When is Kim Jun-hyun coming?

940
01:26:20,947 --> 01:26:22,237
My gosh, this is cool.

941
01:26:23,074 --> 01:26:23,954
Excuse me.

942
01:26:25,410 --> 01:26:28,000
Are they shooting
The Guys Who Died After Eating here?

943
01:26:28,079 --> 01:26:31,039
Yes, are you also here
to get Kim Jun-hyun's autograph?

944
01:26:31,750 --> 01:26:33,960
A person I know is a fan of his.

945
01:26:34,044 --> 01:26:36,594
-His girlfriend is a fan of his.
-My mom is a huge fan.

946
01:26:36,671 --> 01:26:37,801
My dad is a fan.

947
01:26:41,092 --> 01:26:43,472
My boss is a fan. She likes him a lot.

948
01:26:43,887 --> 01:26:45,007
Hey, you guys.

949
01:26:45,096 --> 01:26:46,716
He's over there giving out his autographs.

950
01:26:46,807 --> 01:26:47,927
-Let's go.
-Come on.

951
01:26:48,266 --> 01:26:49,516
Sir, you should come.

952
01:27:08,537 --> 01:27:10,117
Maybe I should've gotten his autograph.

953
01:27:11,248 --> 01:27:12,498
She would've liked it.

954
01:27:19,047 --> 01:27:20,087
Jang Man-wol?

955
01:27:24,010 --> 01:27:26,760
What are you doing here?
Did you know that I was here?

956
01:27:28,306 --> 01:27:29,306
I heard.

957
01:27:30,308 --> 01:27:31,308
Did you meet?

958
01:27:31,393 --> 01:27:33,653
Well, yes. Kind of.

959
01:27:34,437 --> 01:27:35,767
You must've been so happy.

960
01:27:37,107 --> 01:27:38,227
So how was it?

961
01:27:38,567 --> 01:27:40,107
A lot leaner than I thought.

962
01:27:40,193 --> 01:27:42,403
With a small face and great skin.

963
01:27:42,779 --> 01:27:46,199
Why don't you go see for yourself?
I'm sure he's still there. Let's go.

964
01:27:46,283 --> 01:27:48,033
Forget it. Why would I?

965
01:27:48,535 --> 01:27:50,535
I came out to eat webfoot octopus.

966
01:27:51,288 --> 01:27:52,328
Webfoot octopus?

967
01:27:53,498 --> 01:27:56,538
You want to eat webfoot octopus
dressed like that at this late hour?

968
01:27:56,626 --> 01:28:00,206
That's right. Webfoot octopus.
That's the only reason I'm here.

969
01:28:04,384 --> 01:28:05,724
That's the earring I found.

970
01:28:07,429 --> 01:28:08,429
Oh, yes.

971
01:28:08,888 --> 01:28:11,638
I bought these to wear them
when I go out to eat webfoot octopus.

972
01:28:11,850 --> 01:28:14,140
I'm headed to eat webfoot octopus
since I found these earrings.

973
01:28:14,227 --> 01:28:16,057
You must come with me
because you found it.

974
01:28:16,605 --> 01:28:18,515
You're just craving webfoot octopus.

975
01:28:18,607 --> 01:28:21,147
Stop coming up with excuses
that make no sense.

976
01:28:21,234 --> 01:28:23,324
Why? Are you sick and tired of me?

977
01:28:23,445 --> 01:28:25,025
You can't stand me anymore?

978
01:28:29,868 --> 01:28:31,578
If you want to eat webfoot octopus now,

979
01:28:32,412 --> 01:28:33,962
we should go to Noryangjin.

980
01:28:34,247 --> 01:28:36,497
Actually, no.
The west coast is famous for them.

981
01:28:36,958 --> 01:28:37,998
You want to go to the sea?

982
01:28:40,170 --> 01:28:42,130
Well, okay.

983
01:28:43,506 --> 01:28:45,426
And we can see the sunrise too
while we're there.

984
01:28:45,550 --> 01:28:47,550
I'm not sure
if we can see it on the west coast.

985
01:28:48,511 --> 01:28:49,391
But let's go.

986
01:28:52,390 --> 01:28:53,310
Sure.

987
01:28:54,017 --> 01:28:56,267
We'll take that poop colored car you love.

988
01:28:56,561 --> 01:28:58,521
Let's go have some webfoot octopus.

989
01:29:00,398 --> 01:29:01,518
Yes, let's go.

990
01:29:01,900 --> 01:29:05,030
By the way, are you sure
you don't want to see Kim Jun-hyun?

991
01:29:06,071 --> 01:29:07,111
Kim Jun-hyun?

992
01:29:08,114 --> 01:29:09,664
How can I see him?

993
01:29:09,741 --> 01:29:11,911
Didn't you come here to see him?

994
01:29:12,494 --> 01:29:13,874
He's filming something over there.

995
01:29:15,038 --> 01:29:16,828
Darn it. Why didn't you tell me sooner?

996
01:29:19,376 --> 01:29:20,456
Oh, she can run.

997
01:29:21,378 --> 01:29:22,668
Jang Man-wol!

998
01:29:34,557 --> 01:29:37,477
Those are the bowls of hangover soup
he ate here today.

999
01:29:38,478 --> 01:29:41,108
I heard he was chosen again today
for Eat At Once.

1000
01:29:42,607 --> 01:29:44,687
I can't believe I missed it.

1001
01:29:46,486 --> 01:29:49,236
That's where Kim Jun-hyun sat,

1002
01:29:49,489 --> 01:29:51,949
so settle for having
the hangover soup there.

1003
01:29:52,033 --> 01:29:53,203
Eat before it gets cold.

1004
01:29:53,702 --> 01:29:56,042
Then why don't you show me
how much you can eat in one bite?

1005
01:29:56,413 --> 01:29:58,463
With some radish kimchi. Slurp it all in.

1006
01:29:58,540 --> 01:30:00,330
Don't overestimate me, please.

1007
01:30:00,667 --> 01:30:02,587
I'll enjoy this, in many bites.

1008
01:30:07,132 --> 01:30:10,342
This restaurant will do very well
now that Kim Jun-hyun has dined here.

1009
01:30:12,762 --> 01:30:15,642
This restaurant would've done fine
even without Kim Jun-hyun.

1010
01:30:16,641 --> 01:30:17,681
Because of her.

1011
01:30:21,688 --> 01:30:22,768
What about that baby?

1012
01:30:23,106 --> 01:30:24,976
She brings a lot of luck to this place.

1013
01:30:25,066 --> 01:30:27,486
She was born
with a tremendous amount of luck,

1014
01:30:27,569 --> 01:30:29,859
because of all the good karma
she built in her past lives.

1015
01:30:29,946 --> 01:30:32,526
Any family with such a child
becomes successful in no time.

1016
01:30:32,615 --> 01:30:35,195
You can be born with a lot of luck
when you do many good deeds.

1017
01:30:36,494 --> 01:30:38,624
Then in the opposite case...

1018
01:30:38,705 --> 01:30:41,495
You're either born dirt poor
or as a dog or a pig.

1019
01:30:41,624 --> 01:30:43,754
Then if you're reincarnated...

1020
01:30:49,090 --> 01:30:51,470
What? You just thought

1021
01:30:52,010 --> 01:30:54,470
I'd totally be reincarnated
as a dog or a pig, didn't you?

1022
01:30:54,554 --> 01:30:56,684
I'm not sure, but to be honest,
I am worried

1023
01:30:56,765 --> 01:30:57,925
because it's highly likely.

1024
01:30:58,683 --> 01:31:00,983
I've already paid for all my sins
by running the hotel

1025
01:31:01,061 --> 01:31:02,191
for over a millennium.

1026
01:31:02,270 --> 01:31:04,860
But it's not like you've treated
all the guests that well.

1027
01:31:04,939 --> 01:31:06,729
How could I have treated them better?

1028
01:31:08,401 --> 01:31:10,151
You ignored some of them,
saying they're nuisances.

1029
01:31:10,236 --> 01:31:12,156
And you took money
from the rich ones to buy booze

1030
01:31:12,238 --> 01:31:13,448
and cars for yourself.

1031
01:31:14,115 --> 01:31:15,275
I'm really worried about you.

1032
01:31:15,366 --> 01:31:17,236
It's none of your concern.

1033
01:31:17,327 --> 01:31:19,287
It is. I should be concerned.

1034
01:31:19,370 --> 01:31:21,250
I don't want you to be born
as a dog or a pig.

1035
01:31:21,331 --> 01:31:23,371
Gosh, it is none of your business!

1036
01:31:23,500 --> 01:31:25,380
Imagine you being reincarnated as a pig.

1037
01:31:25,502 --> 01:31:27,382
I don't want to meet you again
as hangover soup.

1038
01:31:27,587 --> 01:31:28,757
Be nice.

1039
01:31:29,964 --> 01:31:31,174
I don't want this anymore.

1040
01:31:31,382 --> 01:31:32,932
I lost my appetite because of you.

1041
01:31:35,553 --> 01:31:38,263
I saw a ghost
wandering around the area earlier.

1042
01:31:38,348 --> 01:31:39,768
I told him to go to the hotel,

1043
01:31:39,849 --> 01:31:42,099
but you should take him
since you're here anyway.

1044
01:31:42,185 --> 01:31:43,185
Be nice to him.

1045
01:31:45,355 --> 01:31:46,305
Chan-sung.

1046
01:31:48,566 --> 01:31:52,356
You always go talk to ghosts
you don't even know.

1047
01:31:52,445 --> 01:31:53,395
You really shouldn't.

1048
01:31:53,488 --> 01:31:55,118
They could be evil ghosts.

1049
01:31:56,324 --> 01:31:57,414
It's dangerous.

1050
01:32:01,621 --> 01:32:04,331
Does wandering around for a long time
make them evil ghosts?

1051
01:32:04,582 --> 01:32:06,712
Any wandering ghost turns evil
whenever it harms humans.

1052
01:32:07,168 --> 01:32:09,708
And such a ghost
can devour all other souls,

1053
01:32:09,796 --> 01:32:11,456
let alone living humans.

1054
01:32:12,298 --> 01:32:13,798
If it's caught by the Grim Reaper,

1055
01:32:14,509 --> 01:32:17,639
it certainly won't be reincarnated
as a lucky child or even as an animal.

1056
01:32:18,138 --> 01:32:20,268
Its soul will be perished on the spot.

1057
01:32:28,273 --> 01:32:32,323
Why didn't you report to me
that this room's guest left the hotel?

1058
01:32:32,569 --> 01:32:35,609
It was due to our human manager's mistake.

1059
01:32:35,697 --> 01:32:38,197
What can we do? She left the hotel.

1060
01:32:41,286 --> 01:32:44,246
Her soul is filled with hatred
and resentment toward humans.

1061
01:32:44,581 --> 01:32:47,541
If she causes any trouble
in the outside world,

1062
01:32:47,625 --> 01:32:49,335
I will hold the hotel accountable.

1063
01:32:55,258 --> 01:32:56,628
What a headache.

1064
01:32:56,801 --> 01:32:59,261
The Grim Reaper will manage to catch her
and bring her back.

1065
01:32:59,429 --> 01:33:01,139
If she causes trouble before she's caught

1066
01:33:01,222 --> 01:33:03,062
and turns into an evil ghost,
we'll be doomed.

1067
01:33:03,892 --> 01:33:06,392
She's a dangerous one,
but I feel so bad for her.

1068
01:33:07,562 --> 01:33:11,112
I hope the guest from Room 13
returns safely.

1069
01:33:18,698 --> 01:33:20,618
HOT NEW RELEASES. ENJOY.

1070
01:33:24,287 --> 01:33:26,207
Shall I take a quick break?

1071
01:33:28,917 --> 01:33:31,037
REAL HOT STUFF

1072
01:33:31,127 --> 01:33:32,167
What's this?

1073
01:33:43,264 --> 01:33:44,474
She's taking her clothes off.

1074
01:33:47,560 --> 01:33:49,060
Turn around. Let me see your face.

1075
01:34:02,951 --> 01:34:03,951
Are you enjoying this?

1076
01:34:10,041 --> 01:34:11,081
You like this?

1077
01:34:12,877 --> 01:34:13,957
I'm hot, aren't I?

1078
01:35:22,322 --> 01:35:25,242
ARE YOU GOING TO PICK ME UP AGAIN TODAY?

1079
01:35:25,325 --> 01:35:27,735
WHEN WILL YOU BE HERE?

1080
01:35:27,827 --> 01:35:30,867
I CAN SKIP THE AFTERNOON CLASSES

1081
01:35:31,956 --> 01:35:33,826
How dare a ghost ignore my messages?

1082
01:35:36,085 --> 01:35:37,995
I'm telling you. Yu-na is possessed.

1083
01:35:38,379 --> 01:35:39,759
I got goosebumps all over that day.

1084
01:35:41,299 --> 01:35:44,389
-How about I throw this at her?
-Good idea, try it.

1085
01:35:44,469 --> 01:35:45,599
Let's see what happens.

1086
01:35:45,678 --> 01:35:47,558
-All right, here I go.
-Do it.

1087
01:35:50,433 --> 01:35:51,433
Just a second.

1088
01:35:52,018 --> 01:35:53,898
-Did you get a text?
-No, it's not me.

1089
01:35:53,978 --> 01:35:55,728
-It's not me either.
-Same here.

1090
01:35:55,855 --> 01:35:57,065
I didn't get anything either.

1091
01:35:57,398 --> 01:35:59,648
-What is this, then?
-What's going on?

1092
01:36:08,242 --> 01:36:09,792
Other girls hate her so much.

1093
01:36:12,955 --> 01:36:14,245
I'M HERE BEHIND YOU

1094
01:36:29,138 --> 01:36:31,888
I got Ms. Jang's permission
that you can come to the hotel.

1095
01:36:32,308 --> 01:36:34,478
All right. Let's go there now, then.

1096
01:36:34,644 --> 01:36:36,604
Now? But what about your classes?

1097
01:36:36,687 --> 01:36:39,567
Didn't you see earlier?
I'm struggling to fit in anyway.

1098
01:36:40,233 --> 01:36:41,693
I might as well quit school.

1099
01:36:42,360 --> 01:36:46,030
It's because of the friends
that bully you, right?

1100
01:36:47,448 --> 01:36:49,778
They're quite annoying, but it's fine.

1101
01:36:50,576 --> 01:36:53,696
The real Kim Yu-na was a bad girl.

1102
01:36:54,664 --> 01:36:56,754
I'm actually enjoying seeing
how much Yu-na

1103
01:36:57,041 --> 01:36:58,631
is hated by others.

1104
01:37:02,922 --> 01:37:05,682
It's just that school is boring.

1105
01:37:05,883 --> 01:37:07,643
Why do you think school is boring?

1106
01:37:08,010 --> 01:37:09,970
I had so much fun
back when I was in school.

1107
01:37:10,471 --> 01:37:12,601
I studied and played sports.

1108
01:37:13,141 --> 01:37:14,771
I always came home so late from school

1109
01:37:14,851 --> 01:37:17,191
that the chief servant
had to come to get me.

1110
01:37:18,938 --> 01:37:20,268
"Chief servant"?

1111
01:37:21,399 --> 01:37:23,149
Yes, he was the chief servant in my house.

1112
01:37:23,526 --> 01:37:25,896
He was in a relationship
with my sister's nanny.

1113
01:37:26,362 --> 01:37:28,572
I remember he always fought
with my dad's driver.

1114
01:37:29,323 --> 01:37:30,783
They were in a love triangle.

1115
01:37:34,245 --> 01:37:38,115
A chief servant, a nanny,
and a driver too?

1116
01:37:38,541 --> 01:37:40,751
I guess you were a son of a nobleman
when you were alive.

1117
01:37:43,880 --> 01:37:45,670
You were born
with a golden spoon in your mouth.

1118
01:37:46,174 --> 01:37:48,094
No, it was a silver spoon.

1119
01:37:48,509 --> 01:37:50,679
All of the spoons at my house were silver.

1120
01:37:51,471 --> 01:37:54,351
You were born into a rich family
with a silver spoon in your mouth,

1121
01:37:54,432 --> 01:37:56,682
but you must've been disappointed
to have lived a short life.

1122
01:38:02,273 --> 01:38:05,783
Yes. I am so disappointed
that I can't seem to let it go.

1123
01:38:06,819 --> 01:38:08,699
I can't even go to school
even if I wanted to,

1124
01:38:08,779 --> 01:38:10,409
so try to have a better time at school.

1125
01:38:16,662 --> 01:38:18,582
Schools these days are so nice.

1126
01:38:18,748 --> 01:38:20,368
You guys wear nice school uniforms.

1127
01:38:21,584 --> 01:38:23,094
And you have a great piano like this one.

1128
01:38:26,714 --> 01:38:29,384
This piano is better
than the one at my house.

1129
01:38:31,302 --> 01:38:32,472
Well,

1130
01:38:33,304 --> 01:38:35,644
it sounds like you learned
how to play piano too.

1131
01:38:38,893 --> 01:38:39,983
Play it.

1132
01:38:42,188 --> 01:38:44,938
I don't know how to play it,
but I'll listen to it if you play.

1133
01:38:45,024 --> 01:38:46,444
I've probably forgotten everything.

1134
01:38:46,734 --> 01:38:48,864
Come on, rich boy. Play the piano.

1135
01:38:53,574 --> 01:38:55,084
Who are you talking to now?

1136
01:38:58,829 --> 01:39:01,539
What are you talking about?
I was playing the piano.

1137
01:39:03,459 --> 01:39:05,879
Sure. Play it then.

1138
01:39:07,046 --> 01:39:09,376
Go ahead, Yu-na.
You're good at playing the piano.

1139
01:39:09,465 --> 01:39:10,625
Play the piano.

1140
01:39:25,898 --> 01:39:28,318
-See?
-I was right.

1141
01:40:08,641 --> 01:40:10,351
Hey, she can really play.

1142
01:40:24,362 --> 01:40:26,452
You're pretty good, rich boy.

1143
01:40:26,531 --> 01:40:28,531
See? You didn't forget it.

1144
01:40:31,536 --> 01:40:32,696
I guess not.

1145
01:40:33,579 --> 01:40:35,159
I can't seem to forget this.

1146
01:40:39,585 --> 01:40:41,045
Hyeon-jung!

1147
01:40:53,015 --> 01:40:55,765
Will you ride the bicycle with me
even when you're grown up, Hyeon-mi?

1148
01:40:56,227 --> 01:40:57,267
Yes!

1149
01:40:58,229 --> 01:41:00,309
You have to ride it with me.
You made a promise to me.

1150
01:41:01,065 --> 01:41:02,685
Young Master! Over here!

1151
01:41:02,984 --> 01:41:04,244
Young Lady!

1152
01:41:53,534 --> 01:41:54,994
Don't you think it's better

1153
01:41:55,077 --> 01:41:58,367
if I train Ms. Fourth Choice?
Hyeon-jung is too young for this.

1154
01:41:58,456 --> 01:42:01,456
I'm sure she'll see more eye to eye
with Hyeon-jung,

1155
01:42:01,542 --> 01:42:03,752
who had been educated in the modern times.

1156
01:42:03,836 --> 01:42:05,626
You're too old for her.

1157
01:42:05,713 --> 01:42:08,473
However, Hyeon-jung is
leaning toward Mr. Third Choice.

1158
01:42:08,549 --> 01:42:11,339
Emotionally,
he's bonding more with Mr. Koo.

1159
01:42:12,053 --> 01:42:14,393
But he has a reason to stay in this world.

1160
01:42:14,555 --> 01:42:17,475
He knows that the hotel might disappear,

1161
01:42:18,184 --> 01:42:20,144
so I doubt that he will side with Mr. Koo.

1162
01:42:20,227 --> 01:42:23,767
You're right. He has to stay at the hotel
until that day.

1163
01:42:24,857 --> 01:42:25,937
I'm glad

1164
01:42:26,025 --> 01:42:28,525
that there aren't more changes
after the leaves grew out.

1165
01:42:36,786 --> 01:42:38,246
What's going on?

1166
01:42:38,537 --> 01:42:40,407
Ms. Jang must be angry.

1167
01:42:40,498 --> 01:42:42,458
But she's with Mr. Koo now.

1168
01:42:42,541 --> 01:42:45,171
I guess Mr. Third Choice
must have gotten her riled up.

1169
01:42:45,294 --> 01:42:49,344
I hope she burns with rage
so the leaves fall off the branches.

1170
01:42:57,515 --> 01:42:59,515
We must sell off the cars you don't need.

1171
01:43:00,685 --> 01:43:02,805
I need every single car here.

1172
01:43:02,895 --> 01:43:07,395
You said you didn't drive seven
of these fourteen cars at all last year.

1173
01:43:07,483 --> 01:43:09,653
They are decorating my parking lot.

1174
01:43:10,403 --> 01:43:11,403
Look.

1175
01:43:11,654 --> 01:43:14,624
I've put these beautiful cars
in the same color.

1176
01:43:14,699 --> 01:43:17,789
And these cars are working hard
to make my parking lot look pretty.

1177
01:43:17,868 --> 01:43:19,328
This is a huge space.

1178
01:43:19,412 --> 01:43:21,792
Imagine there are only three cars
in this big space.

1179
01:43:21,872 --> 01:43:24,632
That will look so empty.

1180
01:43:24,709 --> 01:43:27,499
That's exactly my point.
There's only one owner.

1181
01:43:27,712 --> 01:43:29,922
It makes no sense to have
such a huge parking lot like this.

1182
01:43:31,090 --> 01:43:33,550
Select only three cars
and park them near the storage.

1183
01:43:33,634 --> 01:43:36,974
And we can utilize this space
for our hotel guests.

1184
01:43:39,390 --> 01:43:40,850
Why are you doing this to me?

1185
01:43:41,475 --> 01:43:43,435
Why do you want me to sell off my cars?

1186
01:43:44,478 --> 01:43:46,608
Because your finances are a mess.

1187
01:43:48,774 --> 01:43:50,534
You'll go bankrupt at this rate.

1188
01:43:56,323 --> 01:43:57,623
MANAGER KOO CHAN-SUNG

1189
01:44:02,204 --> 01:44:03,544
It will be difficult to pay off

1190
01:44:03,622 --> 01:44:06,002
your next month's card bills
with the balance we have now.

1191
01:44:06,083 --> 01:44:07,173
What about the painting?

1192
01:44:07,251 --> 01:44:09,341
No one is buying.
It's not as wanted as I expected.

1193
01:44:09,420 --> 01:44:11,010
The gold bars from Kim Yu-na's parents.

1194
01:44:11,088 --> 01:44:13,258
You already bought a car with those.

1195
01:44:13,340 --> 01:44:15,590
Right. What about the black card?

1196
01:44:16,635 --> 01:44:17,795
I sent it back.

1197
01:44:17,887 --> 01:44:21,307
You have to pay for the things
you bought for the wedding.

1198
01:44:22,183 --> 01:44:24,773
Have you gone mad?
Why would you send that back?

1199
01:44:24,852 --> 01:44:27,442
Because I cannot have you reincarnated
as a dog or a pig.

1200
01:44:28,856 --> 01:44:32,356
I won't help you extort money
from people anymore.

1201
01:44:32,526 --> 01:44:35,146
Be kind and cut down on your spending.

1202
01:44:38,616 --> 01:44:39,946
Hey, Chan-sung.

1203
01:44:40,785 --> 01:44:42,535
You have nothing to lose.

1204
01:44:42,745 --> 01:44:44,405
What if I get reincarnated
as a dog or a pig?

1205
01:44:44,497 --> 01:44:46,667
I'm fine if I get reincarnated
as a chicken.

1206
01:44:46,749 --> 01:44:49,209
Even if I meet you again
as a bowl of chicken noodles,

1207
01:44:49,293 --> 01:44:52,803
I can say, "Hello, I'm tastier
when you eat me with fresh kimchi."

1208
01:44:52,880 --> 01:44:55,050
I'll say hello to you like this.
I mean it.

1209
01:44:55,216 --> 01:44:57,636
If you don't sell off your cars
and settle your bills,

1210
01:44:57,718 --> 01:45:00,848
you won't even have money
to buy chicken noodles next month.

1211
01:45:08,604 --> 01:45:10,314
Will I be poor again?

1212
01:45:11,232 --> 01:45:13,032
Oh, no. I hate being broke.

1213
01:45:14,652 --> 01:45:16,862
Chan-sung, you're lying, right?

1214
01:45:17,404 --> 01:45:19,284
You're just trying to scare me, right?

1215
01:45:19,406 --> 01:45:22,656
Ms. Jang wasn't always well-off.

1216
01:45:23,452 --> 01:45:26,832
When I came to the hotel,
things were rough.

1217
01:45:26,914 --> 01:45:29,294
Back then, things were really tough.

1218
01:45:29,375 --> 01:45:31,705
As things were chaotic,
we didn't have a human manager.

1219
01:45:31,794 --> 01:45:35,264
Ms. Jang went through a lot.

1220
01:45:44,557 --> 01:45:47,517
I would kill for a bowl of makgeolli
and radish kimchi.

1221
01:45:47,643 --> 01:45:50,653
When the US Army truck passes by later,

1222
01:45:50,729 --> 01:45:52,399
I'll try to get some food.

1223
01:45:53,607 --> 01:45:57,067
The newbie can speak English
since he was educated recently.

1224
01:46:03,534 --> 01:46:05,204
MAN-WOL HOSTEL

1225
01:46:05,286 --> 01:46:06,366
You're pretty good.

1226
01:46:07,079 --> 01:46:08,499
I'll keep you.

1227
01:46:23,679 --> 01:46:24,969
I hate being poor.

1228
01:46:26,348 --> 01:46:29,188
I'm going to keep eating
caviar and champagne.

1229
01:46:33,230 --> 01:46:34,730
When she didn't have enough money,

1230
01:46:34,815 --> 01:46:36,815
she managed to get by
with kimchi and makgeolli.

1231
01:46:37,318 --> 01:46:39,198
I should push her even more.

1232
01:46:40,779 --> 01:46:43,069
Then, Ms. Jang will hate you.

1233
01:46:43,574 --> 01:46:45,204
You could get kicked out at this rate--

1234
01:46:45,910 --> 01:46:48,750
You're doing a great job.
You're truly loyal to her.

1235
01:46:49,205 --> 01:46:52,325
I can take care of her current finances.

1236
01:46:52,416 --> 01:46:54,956
But can the hotel be
in a financial problem?

1237
01:46:55,044 --> 01:46:56,254
When there was a war,

1238
01:46:56,337 --> 01:46:59,007
a tremendous number of people died.

1239
01:46:59,089 --> 01:47:01,679
And none of them died
without regrets and grudges in this world.

1240
01:47:01,800 --> 01:47:04,430
But when that happened,
the door to the afterlife opened wide,

1241
01:47:04,512 --> 01:47:06,972
so not that many souls came to our hotel.

1242
01:47:07,681 --> 01:47:10,271
We managed to get past
that difficult time together.

1243
01:47:10,351 --> 01:47:13,481
You did very well too, Mr. Kim.

1244
01:47:14,188 --> 01:47:16,648
You were the one
who had the most difficult time.

1245
01:47:17,107 --> 01:47:19,687
Let's not be picky with our guests

1246
01:47:19,777 --> 01:47:21,777
and protect our hotel the best we can

1247
01:47:21,862 --> 01:47:23,912
until the day we resolve
our sorrows and grudges.

1248
01:47:23,989 --> 01:47:25,029
Here.

1249
01:47:26,909 --> 01:47:27,869
One, two, three.

1250
01:47:27,952 --> 01:47:29,122
We can do it.

1251
01:47:55,187 --> 01:47:56,227
Your Majesty.

1252
01:47:57,231 --> 01:47:59,401
It is well into the night.

1253
01:48:35,185 --> 01:48:36,185
Who's there?

1254
01:48:37,104 --> 01:48:38,234
Stand back...

1255
01:48:40,024 --> 01:48:41,034
Cut!

1256
01:48:46,071 --> 01:48:49,871
Mr. Yu, shouldn't the king
sound more solemn?

1257
01:48:50,826 --> 01:48:53,366
-I'm sorry.
-We'll take a short break.

1258
01:48:54,079 --> 01:48:57,209
You should sound like a king.
Work on it, okay?

1259
01:48:57,708 --> 01:48:59,838
Yes, ma'am.

1260
01:49:00,669 --> 01:49:01,549
My gosh!

1261
01:49:10,846 --> 01:49:14,016
How dare you! How dare...

1262
01:49:17,394 --> 01:49:18,484
Who's there?

1263
01:49:26,070 --> 01:49:27,740
What a relief.

1264
01:49:28,614 --> 01:49:29,784
Who's there?

1265
01:49:32,993 --> 01:49:34,043
How dare you!

1266
01:49:41,168 --> 01:49:44,378
-Who are you?
-Such insolence! Make way!

1267
01:49:45,506 --> 01:49:47,296
-Wasn't it Yu O?
-Yu O!

1268
01:49:48,175 --> 01:49:49,795
-My gosh.
-Yu O?

1269
01:49:50,761 --> 01:49:53,061
-Yu O!
-Wake up.

1270
01:49:53,138 --> 01:49:55,218
-Please wake up.
-Can you hear us?

1271
01:49:55,307 --> 01:49:56,387
-Do something.
-Wake up!

1272
01:49:56,475 --> 01:49:58,435
-Contact his manager. Hurry!
-Goodness.

1273
01:49:58,519 --> 01:50:00,229
-Yu O, wake up.
-Mr. Yu!

1274
01:50:00,312 --> 01:50:04,782
Why isn't there anyone who can hear me?

1275
01:50:05,567 --> 01:50:07,897
Yu O, come back to us.

1276
01:50:32,928 --> 01:50:34,008
Welcome!

1277
01:50:42,521 --> 01:50:43,361
A king?

1278
01:50:46,191 --> 01:50:47,481
How dare you!

1279
01:50:56,577 --> 01:50:59,117
Ms. Choe, what's happening?

1280
01:50:59,204 --> 01:51:03,174
A VVIP has come to our hotel.

1281
01:51:08,380 --> 01:51:10,010
"A VVIP"?

1282
01:51:11,300 --> 01:51:13,050
A king has come to our hotel.

1283
01:51:13,135 --> 01:51:15,595
I was never able to see one while I lived,

1284
01:51:15,679 --> 01:51:17,099
but now I get the chance.

1285
01:51:17,181 --> 01:51:20,101
A big score has entered the hotel.
Gather everyone.

1286
01:51:20,267 --> 01:51:22,977
We'll provide the VVIP
with the best service

1287
01:51:23,061 --> 01:51:25,061
and have him thoroughly satisfied.

1288
01:51:38,368 --> 01:51:41,868
Your Majesty!

1289
01:51:46,251 --> 01:51:48,921
It's an honor to accommodate
someone of your status.

1290
01:51:49,213 --> 01:51:51,763
I am the owner of this hotel,

1291
01:51:51,840 --> 01:51:55,550
Jang Man-wol.

1292
01:52:00,140 --> 01:52:01,180
A king?

1293
01:52:02,851 --> 01:52:04,851
Tae, Jeong, Tae, Se, Mun, Dan, Se.

1294
01:52:06,313 --> 01:52:07,403
Which King could he be?

1295
01:52:07,564 --> 01:52:11,574
You must be exhausted.
Allow me to escort you to your room.

1296
01:52:50,858 --> 01:52:54,238
Your Majesty,
we have brought you your meal.

1297
01:53:10,002 --> 01:53:11,382
This...

1298
01:53:11,795 --> 01:53:13,005
It's a chamber pot.

1299
01:53:13,380 --> 01:53:15,050
I know he won't need to use it,

1300
01:53:15,132 --> 01:53:17,302
but I thought
it'll bring him some comfort.

1301
01:53:18,385 --> 01:53:20,095
That is very considerate of you.

1302
01:53:20,178 --> 01:53:23,428
Now that I've served the king,
I wouldn't even mind dying...

1303
01:53:24,016 --> 01:53:27,096
Well, I'm already dead,
but that's just how delighted I am.

1304
01:53:31,481 --> 01:53:32,771
Your Majesty.

1305
01:53:34,776 --> 01:53:38,356
I don't want our energy disrupted here,
so don't accept any more new guests.

1306
01:53:38,447 --> 01:53:40,567
Tell them to come back
after the king leaves.

1307
01:53:40,699 --> 01:53:41,619
Yes, ma'am.

1308
01:53:47,205 --> 01:53:48,325
Jang Man-wol.

1309
01:53:49,207 --> 01:53:51,417
You shouldn't refuse our guests like this.

1310
01:53:51,501 --> 01:53:53,001
Well, I can.

1311
01:53:53,629 --> 01:53:56,339
I'm busy here, so go home
if you're going to nag me.

1312
01:53:56,882 --> 01:53:59,592
He's dressed like a king of Joseon.
Which one is he?

1313
01:54:00,260 --> 01:54:01,760
Some were tyrants, you know.

1314
01:54:03,722 --> 01:54:06,562
Nonsense! He didn't seem evil.

1315
01:54:06,934 --> 01:54:10,274
Then did he seem generous and wise?

1316
01:54:11,563 --> 01:54:12,563
Well...

1317
01:54:13,649 --> 01:54:16,819
Why are you nitpicking again?
What's wrong this time?

1318
01:54:17,319 --> 01:54:18,609
You must be clueless.

1319
01:54:19,112 --> 01:54:22,532
Well, it's understandable. It must be
your first time to serve a king guest.

1320
01:54:24,326 --> 01:54:27,246
Have you served one
while working at a hotel then?

1321
01:54:27,621 --> 01:54:28,461
Of course.

1322
01:54:29,331 --> 01:54:32,211
I've served a few members
of Dubai's royal family.

1323
01:54:33,710 --> 01:54:34,630
So?

1324
01:54:34,711 --> 01:54:37,011
Are you seriously bragging about it?

1325
01:54:37,255 --> 01:54:39,125
-That's not it--
-Enough.

1326
01:54:39,633 --> 01:54:41,393
Then you don't know jack.

1327
01:54:41,468 --> 01:54:42,468
Dismissed!

1328
01:54:44,262 --> 01:54:47,352
Chan-sung,
the painting of Baekdu Mountain...

1329
01:54:48,767 --> 01:54:50,017
Sell it at half price.

1330
01:54:50,727 --> 01:54:52,477
Don't come to work until you do.

1331
01:54:58,026 --> 01:55:00,486
They're just too excited
because of the king.

1332
01:55:02,030 --> 01:55:05,240
His Majesty's presence
will make the flowers bloom in the garden.

1333
01:55:05,325 --> 01:55:07,615
Making sure he rests well
before leaving for the afterlife

1334
01:55:07,703 --> 01:55:08,663
is most important.

1335
01:55:08,787 --> 01:55:10,077
Ms. Jang!

1336
01:55:10,497 --> 01:55:12,707
I had him sign the hotel register.

1337
01:55:13,709 --> 01:55:14,669
HOTEL REGISTER

1338
01:55:14,751 --> 01:55:17,841
So his name is Yi Hyeon.

1339
01:55:19,339 --> 01:55:20,469
"Yi Hyeon"?

1340
01:55:21,758 --> 01:55:23,428
Which King was Yi Hyeon?

1341
01:55:23,927 --> 01:55:25,507
It sounds somewhat familiar.

1342
01:55:26,138 --> 01:55:27,058
Let me see.

1343
01:55:27,639 --> 01:55:30,809
Han Suk-kyu played Yi Do,
Lee Seo-jin played Yi San,

1344
01:55:30,892 --> 01:55:33,602
-and Kim Soo-hyun played Yi Hwon.
-Soo-hyun doesn't count.

1345
01:55:33,687 --> 01:55:37,067
It was a character
made up for that particular series.

1346
01:55:37,566 --> 01:55:40,816
Right, a fusion historical drama.
I'm aware of that.

1347
01:55:41,987 --> 01:55:43,947
So who's Yi Hyeon? Did you look it up?

1348
01:55:44,322 --> 01:55:45,532
I found him.

1349
01:55:45,741 --> 01:55:49,041
Right? I knew he existed.

1350
01:55:49,578 --> 01:55:52,208
He's a character from a TV series.

1351
01:55:55,917 --> 01:55:56,917
Let me see that.

1352
01:55:58,420 --> 01:56:00,090
The Crowned Queen?

1353
01:56:02,632 --> 01:56:04,012
Oh, that's right.

1354
01:56:04,134 --> 01:56:06,604
The king from this series
goes by the name Yi Hyeon.

1355
01:56:07,054 --> 01:56:09,014
He is a king!

1356
01:56:09,598 --> 01:56:13,978
Yi Hyeon is just like
Yi Hwon from earlier.

1357
01:56:14,061 --> 01:56:17,981
He's a TV character
from a fusion historical drama.

1358
01:56:19,566 --> 01:56:20,606
What?

1359
01:56:25,864 --> 01:56:30,164
The Crowned Queen is about a queen

1360
01:56:30,243 --> 01:56:32,413
who hires a kisaeng who looks similar

1361
01:56:32,496 --> 01:56:35,666
to take her place in the palace
in order to stay safe.

1362
01:56:36,416 --> 01:56:38,956
Yi Hyeon is the name of the king

1363
01:56:39,044 --> 01:56:40,634
who is her husband.

1364
01:56:41,588 --> 01:56:43,258
Then who is that king that just came in?

1365
01:56:43,340 --> 01:56:44,840
Why does he say he is Yi Hyeon?

1366
01:56:45,258 --> 01:56:49,548
The guest who came to the hotel is
the actor Bang Tae-u.

1367
01:56:51,723 --> 01:56:53,483
The actor Bang Tae-u has

1368
01:56:53,558 --> 01:56:56,228
mostly played minor roles
and supporting roles.

1369
01:56:56,311 --> 01:57:00,111
The first leading role he had
was the role of King Yi Hyeon.

1370
01:57:00,190 --> 01:57:03,240
However, sadly,
before the filming even started,

1371
01:57:03,318 --> 01:57:05,698
he had a cardiac arrest while working out.

1372
01:57:06,404 --> 01:57:07,744
He died suddenly.

1373
01:57:08,657 --> 01:57:11,737
You mean he is not really a king.

1374
01:57:12,327 --> 01:57:15,707
He was an actor who put his soul
into acting to take

1375
01:57:16,039 --> 01:57:17,079
the role of a king.

1376
01:57:17,165 --> 01:57:21,495
The way he talked and walked
was perfectly like a king.

1377
01:57:21,586 --> 01:57:24,166
He died while he was
so immersed in the role.

1378
01:57:24,256 --> 01:57:28,466
I believe he thinks he is a real king.

1379
01:57:35,100 --> 01:57:37,690
This is so embarrassing.

1380
01:57:38,061 --> 01:57:40,901
After we serve him breakfast tomorrow,
send him off

1381
01:57:41,356 --> 01:57:42,436
to the afterlife.

1382
01:58:03,044 --> 01:58:04,254
I heard he was not a king.

1383
01:58:05,338 --> 01:58:07,128
You should have recognized it right away

1384
01:58:07,215 --> 01:58:08,755
when I voiced my suspicions.

1385
01:58:08,842 --> 01:58:09,842
Good for you.

1386
01:58:09,968 --> 01:58:13,008
I didn't send back the guests
who had come, just in case.

1387
01:58:13,096 --> 01:58:15,176
You see, I handled it very wisely.

1388
01:58:15,265 --> 01:58:16,805
I said, good for you!

1389
01:58:16,975 --> 01:58:20,145
When I saw him earlier,
there was a small scar on his face.

1390
01:58:20,228 --> 01:58:21,688
You didn't see it, right?

1391
01:58:22,147 --> 01:58:24,937
It was impossible for a king
to have a scar on his face

1392
01:58:25,025 --> 01:58:26,475
in Joseon Dynasty.

1393
01:58:26,693 --> 01:58:28,073
You know Deposed Queen Lady Yun, right?

1394
01:58:28,153 --> 01:58:30,033
You should know since you love dramas.

1395
01:58:30,113 --> 01:58:32,163
I know her. She was Prince Gwanghae's mom.

1396
01:58:32,240 --> 01:58:33,280
It was Prince Yeonsan's.

1397
01:58:33,825 --> 01:58:36,655
You should have checked which king he was.

1398
01:58:36,745 --> 01:58:38,705
I thought you felt the energy of ghosts.

1399
01:58:38,788 --> 01:58:40,248
But you were fooled by an actor.

1400
01:58:42,876 --> 01:58:44,456
It looked so real.

1401
01:58:45,170 --> 01:58:47,170
Do you know he put his soul
into his acting?

1402
01:58:47,255 --> 01:58:50,875
Think about it.
He must have wanted that role so badly

1403
01:58:50,967 --> 01:58:52,927
that he thinks he's a king
even after he died.

1404
01:58:53,470 --> 01:58:55,640
Why do you look down on a ghost
giving such a performance?

1405
01:58:55,722 --> 01:58:57,562
How dare you? Who do you think you are?

1406
01:58:59,100 --> 01:59:00,100
I am

1407
01:59:00,227 --> 01:59:02,397
just saying I recognized
that he wasn't a king.

1408
01:59:02,479 --> 01:59:06,189
If a guest says he is a king,
a hotelier should treat him like one.

1409
01:59:06,316 --> 01:59:08,106
Whether he is Mansour
or a king from a drama.

1410
01:59:08,276 --> 01:59:10,106
The guests in our hotel are all kings!

1411
01:59:14,950 --> 01:59:18,040
Since when did she ever treat
our guests like kings?

1412
01:59:28,672 --> 01:59:30,762
YU O IS SUCH A BAD ACTOR.
I'M SICK OF YU'S TERRIBLE ACTING.

1413
01:59:30,840 --> 01:59:33,470
A popular star took up the role,
and his acting is terrible.

1414
01:59:33,551 --> 01:59:34,801
He is being criticized so much.

1415
01:59:38,348 --> 01:59:39,638
If he acted that role,

1416
01:59:40,558 --> 01:59:42,848
he would've performed
as if he was possessed.

1417
01:59:50,694 --> 01:59:52,614
Performing as if he was possessed...

1418
01:59:53,863 --> 01:59:54,993
Would that be possible?

1419
02:00:01,538 --> 02:00:04,078
I repented a lot after talking to you.

1420
02:00:04,749 --> 02:00:06,249
When you said guests were our kings,

1421
02:00:07,210 --> 02:00:08,500
I was also moved.

1422
02:00:10,130 --> 02:00:12,050
Then you should work harder in the future.

1423
02:00:12,132 --> 02:00:13,302
So I've been thinking.

1424
02:00:14,259 --> 02:00:16,799
If the guest wants to act,

1425
02:00:16,886 --> 02:00:18,426
we have to help him realize his wishes.

1426
02:00:21,516 --> 02:00:22,926
We hoteliers

1427
02:00:23,018 --> 02:00:25,598
will help our guests become kings
if that is what they want.

1428
02:00:25,687 --> 02:00:27,017
Whether that is Mansour

1429
02:00:27,939 --> 02:00:29,519
or a king from a drama.

1430
02:00:40,785 --> 02:00:41,785
One more time.

1431
02:00:42,245 --> 02:00:43,995
We need to upload it online.

1432
02:00:45,165 --> 02:00:46,455
Show how tasty it is.

1433
02:00:46,666 --> 02:00:48,076
Okay, one, two, three.

1434
02:00:51,254 --> 02:00:55,094
Yu O's fan club hired Sanchez's restaurant
to send a pizza truck to the filming set.

1435
02:00:55,717 --> 02:00:58,137
So we were able to get into the set
easily.

1436
02:01:00,221 --> 02:01:02,641
What's the use of giving
a "possessed" performance?

1437
02:01:02,724 --> 02:01:04,644
It's not like that his face
will be on screen.

1438
02:01:04,726 --> 02:01:07,306
I should be able to act
like I'm possessed after eating this...

1439
02:01:07,437 --> 02:01:09,647
-I'll do better.
-It's okay. Thanks for the pizza.

1440
02:01:09,731 --> 02:01:11,981
Tell him we'll leave
after he looks around the set

1441
02:01:12,067 --> 02:01:14,187
and the staff have some pizza.

1442
02:01:15,028 --> 02:01:16,028
Ms. Jang.

1443
02:01:16,654 --> 02:01:18,454
It's what the guest wants.

1444
02:01:18,573 --> 02:01:20,083
He's really looking forward to it.

1445
02:01:20,158 --> 02:01:21,618
-Hoteliers should--
-Hey!

1446
02:01:22,035 --> 02:01:23,575
Stop. I get it.

1447
02:01:25,622 --> 02:01:26,922
Look after the pizza truck.

1448
02:01:26,998 --> 02:01:28,458
I'll go get the shooting schedule.

1449
02:01:32,045 --> 02:01:33,835
FOOD TRUCK STAFF
THE CROWNED QUEEN

1450
02:01:35,298 --> 02:01:36,878
Excuse me. Food Truck lady?

1451
02:01:38,468 --> 02:01:41,388
Please take five pizzas
to our costumes staff.

1452
02:01:41,471 --> 02:01:42,471
Thank you.

1453
02:01:42,555 --> 02:01:43,765
Stop there.

1454
02:01:47,769 --> 02:01:48,649
Hey.

1455
02:01:49,104 --> 02:01:51,154
This is not a delivery truck.

1456
02:01:51,314 --> 02:01:54,904
If they want to eat,
they should come and get it themselves.

1457
02:01:56,528 --> 02:01:57,528
Okay.

1458
02:02:01,116 --> 02:02:02,406
How impertinent.

1459
02:02:03,660 --> 02:02:06,160
ENJOY THE PIZZA
AND ACT LIKE YOU'RE POSSESSED

1460
02:02:06,496 --> 02:02:09,416
If he could only act well...

1461
02:02:13,253 --> 02:02:15,343
Sir, it's me, Yu O.

1462
02:02:16,464 --> 02:02:19,264
Did you talk to the writer
about me not filming those scenes?

1463
02:02:20,009 --> 02:02:22,259
I am skipping the last two weeks, right?

1464
02:02:22,887 --> 02:02:25,967
I don't care about the plot of the drama.
It's not my concern.

1465
02:02:26,224 --> 02:02:29,104
Just tell them my injury is serious.

1466
02:02:29,185 --> 02:02:30,185
It's so uncomfortable.

1467
02:02:32,188 --> 02:02:34,978
How can the woman
become a queen when there is no king?

1468
02:02:35,066 --> 02:02:36,066
The money I'll get paid?

1469
02:02:36,526 --> 02:02:38,486
I don't need that few hundred million won.

1470
02:02:38,570 --> 02:02:40,070
I just want out.

1471
02:02:40,822 --> 02:02:41,912
Few hundred million won?

1472
02:02:41,990 --> 02:02:44,240
I don't care if you tell them I'm dead.

1473
02:02:44,409 --> 02:02:47,289
You can tell them Yu O is dead.
I can't do this.

1474
02:02:48,830 --> 02:02:49,910
Wait a minute.

1475
02:02:52,959 --> 02:02:55,039
Even if his face is not seen,

1476
02:02:55,420 --> 02:02:57,800
he still can get paid.

1477
02:03:04,304 --> 02:03:06,434
The king doesn't appear
as much as I thought.

1478
02:03:09,475 --> 02:03:11,725
He only has one scene. Let's help him.

1479
02:03:11,811 --> 02:03:13,351
With this one scene,

1480
02:03:14,022 --> 02:03:17,782
he will have to show how he can act
like he's possessed.

1481
02:03:23,865 --> 02:03:25,655
How did Scene 17 end?

1482
02:03:29,245 --> 02:03:32,915
-Then we can go from here.
-Hurry up.

1483
02:03:33,249 --> 02:03:34,499
We're starting.

1484
02:03:36,544 --> 02:03:40,554
"My queen, you are the only one
I've ever loved." What?

1485
02:03:42,717 --> 02:03:43,837
I'm really bad.

1486
02:03:44,219 --> 02:03:45,679
What am I going to do?

1487
02:03:46,346 --> 02:03:48,176
"You are the only one..."

1488
02:03:51,809 --> 02:03:52,809
The Queen?

1489
02:03:53,561 --> 02:03:55,021
I must ask her to help me.

1490
02:03:59,442 --> 02:04:01,322
Hello, Queen.

1491
02:04:01,861 --> 02:04:04,911
Queen, can you do this with me?

1492
02:04:05,990 --> 02:04:07,240
Ms. Queen.

1493
02:04:15,792 --> 02:04:17,132
Queen.

1494
02:04:20,129 --> 02:04:23,679
Can you go over the script with me?

1495
02:04:23,758 --> 02:04:26,428
The director gets so annoyed with me.
Please help me.

1496
02:04:36,729 --> 02:04:39,359
Scene 42 is an emotional scene.

1497
02:04:39,440 --> 02:04:40,400
Oh, my goodness.

1498
02:04:43,945 --> 02:04:44,855
Who are you?

1499
02:04:45,780 --> 02:04:49,030
Look me in the eye, Your Majesty.

1500
02:04:53,246 --> 02:04:54,246
Your Majesty.

1501
02:05:25,194 --> 02:05:26,204
Your Majesty?

1502
02:05:30,950 --> 02:05:32,580
What is it, my Queen?

1503
02:05:35,580 --> 02:05:39,130
You are the king of all the people
living in this country.

1504
02:05:39,709 --> 02:05:40,749
I am.

1505
02:05:41,336 --> 02:05:44,416
I am Yi Hyeon, the king of this country.

1506
02:05:58,478 --> 02:05:59,558
Your Majesty.

1507
02:06:00,938 --> 02:06:02,858
I am a fake.

1508
02:06:03,775 --> 02:06:05,355
I am not the queen.

1509
02:06:06,944 --> 02:06:09,034
Is that why you wanted to leave my side?

1510
02:06:09,530 --> 02:06:10,950
If I stay with you,

1511
02:06:11,532 --> 02:06:13,492
you will be in danger.

1512
02:06:14,494 --> 02:06:16,294
If you hide in the mountains,

1513
02:06:16,704 --> 02:06:18,754
I will cut down all the trees to find you.

1514
02:06:19,040 --> 02:06:20,500
If you go to the seas,

1515
02:06:21,292 --> 02:06:23,462
I will dry up the sea and stop you.

1516
02:06:24,712 --> 02:06:25,712
Your Majesty.

1517
02:06:29,217 --> 02:06:31,007
I command you as your king.

1518
02:06:33,471 --> 02:06:35,181
Don't leave me alone.

1519
02:06:45,775 --> 02:06:48,235
Cut! Okay!

1520
02:06:49,320 --> 02:06:51,610
Gosh, that was great!

1521
02:06:52,365 --> 02:06:53,945
You were amazing.

1522
02:06:54,450 --> 02:06:55,370
My Queen.

1523
02:06:55,451 --> 02:06:57,331
That was incredible!

1524
02:07:07,463 --> 02:07:08,633
You did great!

1525
02:07:09,424 --> 02:07:11,684
-This is great, isn't it?
-You did an amazing job!

1526
02:07:12,051 --> 02:07:13,931
-What just happened?
-What?

1527
02:07:15,680 --> 02:07:16,680
Are we done?

1528
02:07:18,474 --> 02:07:20,484
Great job!

1529
02:07:28,234 --> 02:07:30,074
You were amazing, Your Majesty.

1530
02:07:41,789 --> 02:07:46,339
His Majesty arrives!

1531
02:08:04,270 --> 02:08:05,270
Do not

1532
02:08:06,230 --> 02:08:08,690
talk to me about dethroning the Queen.

1533
02:08:08,858 --> 02:08:13,028
Your Majesty, Her Majesty is
a woman of lowly status.

1534
02:08:13,112 --> 02:08:17,412
She cannot maintain
the dignity of the royal family.

1535
02:08:17,492 --> 02:08:20,702
Please consider her dethronement,
Your Majesty!

1536
02:08:21,829 --> 02:08:22,999
How dare you?

1537
02:08:25,958 --> 02:08:29,588
Our guest agreed to help him act
until the drama ends?

1538
02:08:33,299 --> 02:08:34,719
Let's see.

1539
02:08:36,052 --> 02:08:38,222
Yes, apparently so.

1540
02:08:38,429 --> 02:08:41,769
Why? I thought she wanted to send him off.

1541
02:08:42,975 --> 02:08:46,055
His face might not appear on TV
even if he acts,

1542
02:08:46,145 --> 02:08:47,605
but she'll gain something else.

1543
02:08:49,607 --> 02:08:52,607
My gosh, this is unbelievable.

1544
02:08:53,152 --> 02:08:57,032
After I went over my lines with you,
I suddenly acted like I was possessed.

1545
02:08:57,114 --> 02:08:58,704
You know what I mean, right?

1546
02:08:58,783 --> 02:09:02,333
I felt like I was possessed
by someone else when I acted.

1547
02:09:03,037 --> 02:09:05,367
By any chance, are you an acting teacher?

1548
02:09:05,456 --> 02:09:06,616
Do you want

1549
02:09:07,416 --> 02:09:08,626
to keep this up?

1550
02:09:08,709 --> 02:09:11,169
Of course. Please do me a favor

1551
02:09:11,254 --> 02:09:13,134
and continue to help me out.

1552
02:09:13,256 --> 02:09:14,296
Then...

1553
02:09:15,132 --> 02:09:17,342
let's start negotiating your pay.

1554
02:09:18,052 --> 02:09:19,102
My pay?

1555
02:09:19,512 --> 02:09:22,102
Oh, sure. I guess you already know.

1556
02:09:22,181 --> 02:09:23,721
You can take everything.

1557
02:09:23,808 --> 02:09:25,888
How much do you get paid for each episode?

1558
02:09:25,977 --> 02:09:28,597
I get paid 120 million won,
and there are 4 episodes for 2 weeks.

1559
02:09:28,688 --> 02:09:31,108
So, 4 times 120 million won is
480 million won in total.

1560
02:09:31,524 --> 02:09:33,404
I guess that will be enough
to rent a house.

1561
02:09:33,568 --> 02:09:35,858
Go ahead and take everything.
It's fine with me.

1562
02:09:37,446 --> 02:09:39,866
Our guest is getting paid for his acting,

1563
02:09:39,949 --> 02:09:41,779
and he's agreed to this.

1564
02:09:42,118 --> 02:09:43,448
So I have no objections.

1565
02:09:43,536 --> 02:09:48,166
Hey, I didn't know actors
got paid that much money.

1566
02:09:49,125 --> 02:09:51,375
Chan-sung,
how about you start a career in acting?

1567
02:09:51,460 --> 02:09:54,050
I don't know how to act.
I'm a horrible actor.

1568
02:09:54,922 --> 02:09:58,472
I guess you're right.
I can tell that you'll be bad at it.

1569
02:09:58,968 --> 02:10:00,218
So, tell me.

1570
02:10:00,636 --> 02:10:04,016
You told me that I don't even have
enough money to buy myself

1571
02:10:04,098 --> 02:10:07,228
a bowl of chicken noodles.
But that was a lie, wasn't it?

1572
02:10:07,310 --> 02:10:09,440
It's true that your loan is overdue.

1573
02:10:10,187 --> 02:10:11,517
But I lied about the chicken noodles.

1574
02:10:12,148 --> 02:10:14,568
You have enough money for webfoot octopus.

1575
02:10:14,859 --> 02:10:16,319
Oh, right. Webfoot octopus.

1576
02:10:16,444 --> 02:10:18,534
I couldn't eat that because of you.

1577
02:10:19,113 --> 02:10:22,123
Yes, you're right. It's all my fault.

1578
02:10:24,368 --> 02:10:26,368
I'll forgive you
since you know you're at fault.

1579
02:10:27,538 --> 02:10:28,868
Then let's go to the west coast.

1580
02:10:29,290 --> 02:10:32,790
We might get lucky and see the sunrise.
We can also eat webfoot octopus.

1581
02:10:33,044 --> 02:10:34,054
What's going on?

1582
02:10:34,712 --> 02:10:35,962
Why are you being so nice?

1583
02:10:39,175 --> 02:10:40,505
Are you suddenly being nice to me

1584
02:10:40,593 --> 02:10:42,643
because I told you
I'm going to be your last guest?

1585
02:10:43,346 --> 02:10:45,386
"We'll give you everything you want."

1586
02:10:45,473 --> 02:10:48,733
Gosh, what an incredible hotelier.

1587
02:10:49,977 --> 02:10:51,597
I'm not that incredible.

1588
02:10:51,896 --> 02:10:56,106
Hoteliers aren't supposed to have
personal feelings for their guests.

1589
02:10:57,902 --> 02:10:58,902
What?

1590
02:11:02,156 --> 02:11:04,826
What kind of personal feelings
do you have for me?

1591
02:11:05,201 --> 02:11:06,241
The leaf.

1592
02:11:08,454 --> 02:11:10,044
You showed me that I got two leaves.

1593
02:11:11,082 --> 02:11:12,502
How do you expect me to ignore that?

1594
02:11:17,546 --> 02:11:20,586
Let's not go today.
I had too much champagne.

1595
02:11:21,217 --> 02:11:24,427
We can have the webfoot octopus tomorrow.

1596
02:11:26,055 --> 02:11:27,925
I need to go to the filming set tomorrow.

1597
02:11:28,015 --> 02:11:29,345
You don't need to go there.

1598
02:11:29,767 --> 02:11:31,437
I hired an intern for you.

1599
02:11:34,814 --> 02:11:36,614
THE CROWNED QUEEN

1600
02:11:42,780 --> 02:11:44,200
You're the intern?

1601
02:11:44,281 --> 02:11:45,281
Yes.

1602
02:11:45,574 --> 02:11:48,244
Feel free to quit whenever you wish.

1603
02:11:48,452 --> 02:11:50,082
I'll take your place.

1604
02:11:50,913 --> 02:11:52,673
You should be in school.

1605
02:11:53,249 --> 02:11:54,789
I'm planning to stay in school.

1606
02:11:57,294 --> 02:12:00,804
I'm doing it for someone
who used to love going to school.

1607
02:12:02,758 --> 02:12:04,798
School's over today,
so I can go with you, right?

1608
02:12:04,885 --> 02:12:06,545
I can't find the hotel on my own
during the day.

1609
02:12:06,637 --> 02:12:09,717
Let's go next time.
I have to meet someone here.

1610
02:12:10,015 --> 02:12:11,135
Who are you meeting?

1611
02:12:11,767 --> 02:12:12,767
A ghost?

1612
02:12:12,852 --> 02:12:14,602
No, it's a human being.
I'm meeting a friend.

1613
02:12:15,730 --> 02:12:18,190
I'm not interested in humans.
See you later.

1614
02:12:20,985 --> 02:12:24,525
I clearly told them to put a space
between "take" and "out."

1615
02:12:24,613 --> 02:12:26,373
-Thank you for the food.
-No problem.

1616
02:12:26,782 --> 02:12:28,992
I heard you're Man-wol's relative.
You should come often.

1617
02:12:29,076 --> 02:12:30,076
Okay.

1618
02:12:31,036 --> 02:12:32,536
Hey, Mi-ra.

1619
02:12:33,289 --> 02:12:35,289
Chan-sung's waiting for you inside.
Go on in.

1620
02:12:57,146 --> 02:12:59,976
I thought he was meeting a friend.
But I guess he meant his girlfriend.

1621
02:13:05,613 --> 02:13:06,863
It's been a while.

1622
02:13:09,909 --> 02:13:10,949
Yes, it has.

1623
02:13:19,460 --> 02:13:22,420
Where are you going, Ms. Jang?
You look like you're in a good mood.

1624
02:13:22,713 --> 02:13:24,673
Yes, I'm going to the beach.

1625
02:13:25,007 --> 02:13:27,217
The beach? There's a beach in our hotel.

1626
02:13:27,551 --> 02:13:29,181
You can't compare that to a real beach.

1627
02:13:29,887 --> 02:13:30,967
How is it different?

1628
02:13:31,055 --> 02:13:32,215
Our beach is...

1629
02:13:35,601 --> 02:13:36,521
Webfoot octopus.

1630
02:13:37,353 --> 02:13:38,903
There's no webfoot octopus here.

1631
02:13:38,979 --> 02:13:40,399
I'm on my way to eat that.

1632
02:13:42,191 --> 02:13:43,821
Should I ask Yu-na to get you some?

1633
02:13:43,984 --> 02:13:46,824
No, I want to eat it there.

1634
02:13:46,904 --> 02:13:49,874
Gosh, it'll be great
if Mr. Koo can drive you there.

1635
02:13:49,949 --> 02:13:51,119
Should I call him?

1636
02:13:51,617 --> 02:13:53,487
There's no need. He'll be here.

1637
02:13:53,577 --> 02:13:55,867
You're right.
We shouldn't call him to hurry

1638
02:13:55,955 --> 02:13:57,405
when he's with his girlfriend.

1639
02:13:58,332 --> 02:14:01,132
Yu-na apparently saw her.
I heard she's really pretty.

1640
02:14:01,877 --> 02:14:04,257
Mr. Koo's always around ghosts,

1641
02:14:04,338 --> 02:14:06,548
so he should meet a lot of humans
when he can.

1642
02:14:07,591 --> 02:14:09,551
If he ends up growing old

1643
02:14:09,635 --> 02:14:12,425
all by himself just like Mr. No did,

1644
02:14:13,013 --> 02:14:14,143
I'd feel so sorry for him.

1645
02:14:17,977 --> 02:14:21,187
Ms. Jang, I hope you eat
a lot of delicious food at the beach.

1646
02:14:21,480 --> 02:14:22,570
Hyeon-jung.

1647
02:14:22,940 --> 02:14:25,860
Tell the guests to empty
the hotel beach within 30 minutes.

1648
02:14:27,027 --> 02:14:28,237
I want to take a rest there.

1649
02:14:28,362 --> 02:14:30,952
I thought you were going to go
to a beach far away.

1650
02:14:31,157 --> 02:14:33,327
Why would I go?
They're all the same anyway.

1651
02:14:34,076 --> 02:14:35,116
I'm...

1652
02:14:36,370 --> 02:14:37,580
not going.

1653
02:14:40,624 --> 02:14:42,334
Should I buy you some webfoot octopus?

1654
02:14:44,253 --> 02:14:46,343
You acted like you were never
going to come back to Korea.

1655
02:14:46,422 --> 02:14:47,262
But here you are.

1656
02:14:47,339 --> 02:14:50,009
Are you nervous to see me here
since it was so unexpected?

1657
02:14:50,092 --> 02:14:51,932
I'm just glad to see you.

1658
02:14:52,887 --> 02:14:54,847
I found it weird
that you suddenly showed up,

1659
02:14:54,930 --> 02:14:56,180
so I asked around.

1660
02:14:56,265 --> 02:14:58,595
I heard you took out a loan
and your parents kicked you out.

1661
02:14:58,684 --> 02:14:59,854
It was only a small amount.

1662
02:15:00,227 --> 02:15:02,477
I'm a doctor.
I'm going to pay it off soon.

1663
02:15:02,563 --> 02:15:04,733
Is that so? That's good to hear.

1664
02:15:05,232 --> 02:15:07,152
I don't have much time,
so let's cut to the chase.

1665
02:15:07,276 --> 02:15:09,526
I want my 5,000 dollars back.

1666
02:15:09,612 --> 02:15:12,242
It's been ages since we last met.
Let's not talk about money.

1667
02:15:12,323 --> 02:15:14,993
I'm talking about money
because it's been a long time.

1668
02:15:15,075 --> 02:15:17,905
Otherwise, I would've sued you.

1669
02:15:17,995 --> 02:15:20,155
I don't believe you.

1670
02:15:20,289 --> 02:15:22,539
I know how much you loved me.

1671
02:15:22,666 --> 02:15:24,416
You'll never sue me.

1672
02:15:26,212 --> 02:15:28,212
Yes. When you told me
your family was in a pickle

1673
02:15:28,297 --> 02:15:30,127
and asked me to lend you 5,000 dollars,

1674
02:15:30,216 --> 02:15:33,716
I liked you so much that I even gave you
money from my tuition.

1675
02:15:33,802 --> 02:15:34,802
Chan-sung.

1676
02:15:35,179 --> 02:15:38,809
Try to remember
how much you liked me back then.

1677
02:15:39,975 --> 02:15:42,725
First, let me calculate
how much you need to pay me back.

1678
02:15:42,811 --> 02:15:44,611
Gosh, I'll pay you back.

1679
02:15:44,730 --> 02:15:47,570
But I actually called you
because I really missed you.

1680
02:15:47,816 --> 02:15:49,276
It's so nice to see you again.

1681
02:15:49,401 --> 02:15:50,781
I guess you're still hopeless.

1682
02:15:50,861 --> 02:15:52,201
And it's still charming, isn't it?

1683
02:15:53,864 --> 02:15:54,874
Okay, fine.

1684
02:15:58,410 --> 02:16:00,960
That's enough. You have a bad stomach.

1685
02:16:02,706 --> 02:16:04,326
You haven't changed either.

1686
02:16:05,501 --> 02:16:09,381
Chan-sung, I heard you're single.

1687
02:16:09,463 --> 02:16:10,463
Just a second.

1688
02:16:25,396 --> 02:16:26,306
Excuse me!

1689
02:16:26,772 --> 02:16:28,022
Wait!

1690
02:16:51,672 --> 02:16:53,302
-Yes?
-Mr. Kim Jun-hyun.

1691
02:16:53,424 --> 02:16:54,514
Yes?

1692
02:16:56,093 --> 02:16:57,263
Can I get an autograph?

1693
02:16:57,386 --> 02:16:58,636
Sure.

1694
02:17:00,180 --> 02:17:01,520
You must have run here.

1695
02:17:03,392 --> 02:17:04,892
Wait. Let me borrow your back.

1696
02:17:04,977 --> 02:17:07,227
-My back?
-Yes. It has to be flat.

1697
02:17:08,314 --> 02:17:09,614
What's your name?

1698
02:17:09,690 --> 02:17:11,730
-It's Jang Man-wol.
-Jang Man-wol.

1699
02:17:11,817 --> 02:17:14,147
She's a huge fan.

1700
02:17:15,070 --> 02:17:17,990
Thank her for me. What a great name.

1701
02:17:18,365 --> 02:17:19,365
Okay.

1702
02:17:20,868 --> 02:17:21,868
Bye.

1703
02:17:22,453 --> 02:17:23,833
-Excuse me.
-Yes?

1704
02:17:24,413 --> 02:17:25,753
Can we take a photo too?

1705
02:17:26,457 --> 02:17:27,747
She doesn't trust people easily.

1706
02:17:27,833 --> 02:17:31,753
She doesn't trust people? I see.
Sure, let's take one.

1707
02:17:31,837 --> 02:17:33,337
People take photos these days.

1708
02:17:34,298 --> 02:17:36,218
How should I pose? All right.

1709
02:17:36,300 --> 02:17:38,260
One, two, three.

1710
02:17:49,897 --> 02:17:51,607
MS. JANG

1711
02:17:53,233 --> 02:17:54,783
I was just about to call you.

1712
02:17:55,652 --> 02:17:58,072
-I just met someone.
-Chan-sung.

1713
02:17:59,406 --> 02:18:01,116
Take the day off. Don't come.

1714
02:18:02,993 --> 02:18:04,753
What about our trip to the sea?

1715
02:18:05,913 --> 02:18:07,623
I can go to the sea at the hotel too.

1716
02:18:07,915 --> 02:18:09,415
It's all the same, anyway.

1717
02:18:09,875 --> 02:18:11,375
I don't have to go. Take the day off.

1718
02:18:18,509 --> 02:18:21,799
TO MS. JANG MAN-WOL, I LOVE YOU

1719
02:19:54,354 --> 02:19:55,614
You're here.

1720
02:19:56,356 --> 02:19:57,856
How did you find me here?

1721
02:19:58,609 --> 02:19:59,939
Yeon-u told me.

1722
02:20:02,613 --> 02:20:05,993
You should have told me first
if you found a good place like this.

1723
02:20:06,533 --> 02:20:07,993
Don't keep it to yourself.

1724
02:20:08,577 --> 02:20:10,367
It's a good place to drink alone.

1725
02:20:11,038 --> 02:20:12,208
Get lost.

1726
02:21:31,159 --> 02:21:35,039
Now do you realize
the view's got better than earlier?

1727
02:21:39,501 --> 02:21:41,881
They are just fireflies.
What's got better?

1728
02:21:42,212 --> 02:21:43,462
Of course it's better.

1729
02:21:43,630 --> 02:21:47,470
Earlier, you were alone.
But now, I'm here with you.

1730
02:21:51,346 --> 02:21:54,466
Every sight you see with me
will look different.

1731
02:22:01,023 --> 02:22:03,943
From now on, drinking alone here
won't make you happy.

1732
02:22:05,110 --> 02:22:06,570
Mark my words.

1733
02:22:08,030 --> 02:22:11,580
You'll be waiting for me
to suddenly show up like today.

1734
02:23:42,541 --> 02:23:46,251
The tree I'm growing
at Guest House of the Moon

1735
02:23:46,628 --> 02:23:48,798
used to be as stiff as a rock.

1736
02:23:49,005 --> 02:23:51,165
But it's starting to look pretty now.

1737
02:23:52,759 --> 02:23:56,809
I guess the man you sent is taking
good care of the tree.

1738
02:23:56,930 --> 02:23:59,020
You sent him there
because you thought he was the remedy,

1739
02:23:59,099 --> 02:24:00,519
but he might turn out to be poison.

1740
02:24:01,935 --> 02:24:06,355
Love can be one's remedy and poison.
That's how it is.

1741
02:24:06,440 --> 02:24:09,070
But it's so hard to weave them together.

1742
02:24:11,278 --> 02:24:13,568
Darn it. It's tangled again.

1743
02:24:14,489 --> 02:24:15,909
Darn it. What should I do?

1744
02:24:16,324 --> 02:24:17,994
Darn it. Goodness.

1745
02:24:23,874 --> 02:24:28,304
RICH BOY, DO YOU WANT
TO GRAB A SANDWICH WITH ME?

1746
02:24:28,503 --> 02:24:32,303
No. Asking a ghost to have
a sandwich with me sounds weird.

1747
02:24:35,010 --> 02:24:36,340
What should I say?

1748
02:24:46,104 --> 02:24:47,114
What was that?

1749
02:24:47,481 --> 02:24:49,611
That felt really creepy just now.

1750
02:24:52,027 --> 02:24:53,147
HEY, ANYTHING FUN THESE DAYS?

1751
02:24:53,236 --> 02:24:54,486
SOMEBODY, SEND ME SOME FUN STUFF

1752
02:24:54,571 --> 02:24:55,911
HERE

1753
02:24:55,989 --> 02:24:58,409
IT'S GOING VIRAL.
BUT IF YOU'RE SCARED, DON'T OPEN IT.

1754
02:24:58,492 --> 02:25:01,242
IT'S THE FAMOUS VIDEO? I DIDN'T WATCH IT.

1755
02:25:01,703 --> 02:25:02,953
He's trying to scare me.

1756
02:25:10,587 --> 02:25:11,627
Are you enjoying this?

1757
02:25:12,547 --> 02:25:13,587
You like this?

1758
02:25:16,384 --> 02:25:17,554
I'm hot, aren't I?

1759
02:25:49,376 --> 02:25:51,916
Ms. Jang is on the beach by herself?

1760
02:25:52,003 --> 02:25:54,303
Yes, she told me not to let anyone in.

1761
02:26:15,151 --> 02:26:17,491
Is this Weather Control Department?
I'm on the beach now.

1762
02:26:17,571 --> 02:26:19,161
The sun is too strong now!

1763
02:26:19,614 --> 02:26:20,994
I don't want 12 p.m.

1764
02:26:22,242 --> 02:26:25,662
How about around 6 p.m.?
Change the setting to sundown.

1765
02:26:38,300 --> 02:26:41,010
Whether the sun is blazing or goes down,

1766
02:26:43,221 --> 02:26:45,471
the beach looks the same.

1767
02:26:47,726 --> 02:26:50,056
I should ask them
to make the waves stronger.

1768
02:26:51,855 --> 02:26:53,355
The beach will still look the same.

1769
02:26:55,942 --> 02:26:57,282
Why are you here?

1770
02:26:57,652 --> 02:26:59,402
You refused to go to the beach with me.

1771
02:27:04,159 --> 02:27:05,239
Because...

1772
02:27:06,661 --> 02:27:07,751
I found it silly.

1773
02:27:07,829 --> 02:27:08,999
Silly?

1774
02:27:09,372 --> 02:27:10,872
You and your capricious mind.

1775
02:27:12,083 --> 02:27:13,793
I told you to rest.
What are you doing here?

1776
02:27:14,502 --> 02:27:16,252
I did something silly,

1777
02:27:17,172 --> 02:27:19,472
but I can't tell you what I did
because you might laugh at me.

1778
02:27:20,508 --> 02:27:21,468
What did you do?

1779
02:27:22,093 --> 02:27:24,933
-Don't laugh.
-I'm not in the mood. What is it?

1780
02:27:33,647 --> 02:27:35,227
TO MS. JANG MAN-WOL, I LOVE YOU.

1781
02:27:41,029 --> 02:27:42,239
Doesn't it make you happy?

1782
02:27:43,573 --> 02:27:46,413
"To Ms. Jang Man-wol, I love you"?

1783
02:27:47,911 --> 02:27:49,331
Are you confessing your love to me?

1784
02:27:49,913 --> 02:27:52,963
No! I didn't write this.

1785
02:27:53,583 --> 02:27:56,003
This is Kim Jun-hyun's autograph.
Here, "Kim Jun-hyun."

1786
02:27:56,670 --> 02:27:57,920
Kim Jun-hyun?

1787
02:28:01,091 --> 02:28:02,131
It's true.

1788
02:28:02,217 --> 02:28:04,757
I ran after him and asked him
for an autograph on the streets

1789
02:28:04,844 --> 02:28:06,224
even though I was so embarrassed.

1790
02:28:06,596 --> 02:28:07,886
I thought it'd make you happy.

1791
02:28:14,562 --> 02:28:15,612
Are you not happy?

1792
02:28:19,818 --> 02:28:20,858
I am.

1793
02:28:23,863 --> 02:28:25,283
I love this.

1794
02:28:30,286 --> 02:28:31,576
I knew you'd like it.

1795
02:28:34,457 --> 02:28:35,877
I felt so shy

1796
02:28:36,626 --> 02:28:38,126
about asking for an autograph.

1797
02:28:45,135 --> 02:28:48,005
It turns out this beach is as nice
as somewhere far.

1798
02:28:48,930 --> 02:28:50,520
Although there's no webfoot octopus here.

1799
02:28:55,979 --> 02:28:57,149
That's okay.

1800
02:28:59,315 --> 02:29:00,815
Because you're here.

1801
02:29:08,616 --> 02:29:10,116
The sea looks really beautiful.

1802
02:29:15,707 --> 02:29:16,917
Yes, indeed.

1803
02:29:20,503 --> 02:29:21,763
It makes me sad.

1804
02:29:32,932 --> 02:29:34,062
I'm...

1805
02:29:37,145 --> 02:29:38,345
a little sad.

1806
02:29:42,233 --> 02:29:44,073
Because the sea...

1807
02:29:46,237 --> 02:29:48,157
looks more beautiful now...

1808
02:29:52,410 --> 02:29:53,750
than it did earlier.

1809
02:31:03,898 --> 02:31:05,688
Since you can see my past,

1810
02:31:05,775 --> 02:31:09,565
you'll gradually find out
how much of a horrible person I was.

1811
02:31:09,654 --> 02:31:10,864
You can't do this here, sir.

1812
02:31:11,614 --> 02:31:12,704
Just leave him be.

1813
02:31:12,782 --> 02:31:15,122
Kill her as much as you want
until you feel better.

1814
02:31:15,201 --> 02:31:17,371
Now... Pick one.

1815
02:31:17,871 --> 02:31:18,911
Lee Mi-ra.

1816
02:31:18,997 --> 02:31:20,537
I invited you to the hotel.

1817
02:31:20,623 --> 02:31:22,583
It's not a place you can come in a dream.

1818
02:31:22,667 --> 02:31:23,997
You can come only when you're dead.

1819
02:31:25,837 --> 02:31:27,837
Subtitle translation by Wayne Ryu
